ify it fails (should only have namespace-scoped permissions)\n339: - [ ] Attempt unauthorized operation and verify it fails\n340: \n341: **Verification**: Controller Manager has correct namespace-scoped permissions\n342: \n343: ---\n344: \n345: ### Task 26: Test RBAC permissions for Router\n346: - [ ] Deploy Router pod with its ServiceAccount\n347: - [ ] Create test secret in namespace\n348: - [ ] Verify Router can get secrets\n349: - [ ] Verify Router can list secrets\n350: - [ ] Verify Router cannot delete secrets (only get/list/watch allowed)\n351: - [ ] Verify Router cannot create secrets\n352: - [ ] Attempt unauthorized operation and verify it fails\n353: \n354: **Verification**: Router has correct read-only permissions for secrets\n355: \n356: ---\n357: \n358: ### Task 27: Verify principle of least privilege\n359: - [ ] Review all ClusterRole rules\n360: - [ ] Verify no wildcard (*) verbs are used unless absolutely necessary\n361: - [ ] Verify no wildcard (*) resources are used\n362: - [ ] Verify all permissions are specific and minimal\n363: - [ ] Review all Role rules\n364: - [ ] Verify permissions are namespace-scoped where possible\n365: - [ ] Document any exceptions to least privilege principle\n366: \n367: **Verification**: All RBAC configurations follow principle of least privilege\n368: \n369: ---\n370: \n371: ### Task 28: Add RBAC upgrade documentation\n372: - [ ] Document RBAC upgrade path in manifests/README.md\n373: - [ ] Document how to upgrade from no-RBAC deployment\n374: - [ ] Document how to upgrade RBAC permissions\n375: - [ ] Document backward compatibility considerations\n376: - [ ] Document how to remove RBAC gracefully\n377: - [ ] Add warning about breaking changes\n378: \n379: **Verification**: RBAC upgrade documentation is complete\n380: \n381: ---\n382: \n383: ### Task 29: Create RBAC values reference\n384: - [ ] Create docs/RBAC_VALUES.md or add to manifests/README.md\n385: - [ ] Document all rbac.* values\n386: - [ ] Document all serviceAccount.* values\n387: - [ ] Document default values\n388: - [ ] Document required values\n389: - [ ] Document optional values\n390: - [ ] Provide examples\n391: \n392: **Verification**: RBAC values reference is complete\n393: \n394: ---\n395: \n396: ### Task 30: Final RBAC validation\n397: - [ ] Run full Helm install with all RBAC features enabled\n398: - [ ] Verify all RBAC resources are created\n399: - [ ] Verify all RBAC resources have correct labels\n400: - [ ] Verify all RBAC resources have correct permissions\n401: - [ ] Verify all components use correct ServiceAccounts\n402: - [ ] Verify all bindings are correct\n403: - [ ] Run permission tests for all components\n404: - [ ] Document any issues found\n405: - [ ] Fix any issues found\n406: \n407: **Verification**: RBAC configuration is complete and functional\n408: \n409: ---\n410: \n411: ### Task 31: Review and document any missing RBAC features\n412: - [ ] Review delta-spec.md for any unimplemented features\n413: - [ ] Check for monitoring RBAC configuration\n414: - [ ] Check for observability RBAC configuration\n415: - [ ] Check for logging RBAC configuration\n416: - [ ] Document any missing features\n417: - [ ] Create follow-up tasks if needed\n418: \n419: **Verification**: All required RBAC features from delta-spec.md are implemented or documented\n420: \n421: ---\n422: \n423: ### Task 32: Clean up test resources\n424: - [ ] Remove test namespaces created during testing\n425: - [ ] Remove test ServiceAccounts created during testing\n426: - [ ] Remove test resources created during testing\n427: - [ ] Verify no orphaned resources remain\n428: \n429: **Verification**: Test environment is clean\n430: \n431: ---\n432: \n433: ### Task 33: Update CHANGE.md\n434: - [ ] Document RBAC configuration implementation\n435: - [ ] List all RBAC resources added\n436: - [ ] Document new Helm values\n437: - [ ] Document backward compatibility\n438: - [ ] Document migration path\n439: \n440: **Verification**: CHANGE.md is updated with RBAC implementation details\n441: \n442: ---\n443: \n444: ## Summary\n445: \n446: **Total Tasks**: 33\n447: **Estimated Effort**: M (Medium) - 15-20 hours\n448: \n449: ### Key Deliverables\n450: 1. **Complete RBAC configuration** for Workload Manager (ServiceAccount, ClusterRole, ClusterRoleBinding)\n451: 2. **Complete RBAC configuration** for Controller Manager (ServiceAccount, Role, RoleBinding)\n452: 3. **Complete RBAC configuration** for Router (ServiceAccount, Role, RoleBinding)\n453: 4. **Helm values configuration** for RBAC (rbac.create, serviceAccount options)\n454: 5. **RBAC documentation** (README, testing checklist, values reference)\n455: 6. **RBAC validation** (syntax, permissions, least privilege)\n456: \n457: ### Success Criteria\n458: - All RBAC templates have valid YAML syntax\n459: - All RBAC resources are created correctly with default Helm values\n460: - RBAC can be enabled/disabled via Helm values\n461: - Custom ServiceAccounts work correctly\n462: - All components have correct permissions (authorized operations succeed, unauthorized operations fail)\n463: - Principle of least privilege is followed\n464: - RBAC is properly documented\n465: - All tests pass\n466: \n467: ### Dependencies\n468: - Kubernetes 1.20+ (RBAC API v1)\n469: - Helm 3.x\n470: - Base design document: `design.md`\n471: - Base specification document: `deployment/spec.md`\n472: - AR: AR-030 — Helm Chart 模板与 Values (for Helm-based RBAC configuration)\n473: \n474: ### Blocked By\n475: - None (design stage ST-3 completed)\n476: \n477: ### Blocks\n478: - AR-032: Workload Manager Deployment (depends on RBAC configuration)\n479: - AR-033: Controller Manager Deployment (depends on RBAC configuration)\n480: - AR-034: Router Deployment (depends on RBAC configuration)\n481: \n482: ### Notes\n483: - RBAC configuration is critical for security in production deployments\n484: - Follow principle of least privilege at all times\n485: - Test RBAC thoroughly before deploying to production\n486: - Document any exceptions to least privilege principle\n487: - RBAC resources are cluster-critical, plan upgrades carefully\n\n(End of file - total 487 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-031 — RBAC 配置 (SA/Role/Binding) Tasks\n\n**Module**: `manifests`\n**Language**: YAML\n**Size**: M\n**Design Stage**: ST-3 Completed\n\n## Task Breakdown\n\n### Task 1: Review existing Workload Manager ServiceAccount template\n- [ ] Review manifests/charts/agentcube/templates/workload-manager/serviceaccount.yaml\n- [ ] Verify template includes proper Helm conditionals (enabled and serviceAccount.create)\n- [ ] Verify template uses correct helper functions (serviceAccountName, namespace, labels)\n- [ ] Verify component label is set to workload-manager\n- [ ] Verify annotations are conditionally included\n- [ ] Document any issues or missing elements\n\n**Verification**: Template follows best practices and matches component pattern\n\n---","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-031/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775883116972,"end":1775883116995}}}}
