{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775883128498,"sessionID":"ses_2851e3b7cffetDjglBtQhaUd1M","part":{"id":"prt_d7ae20eaf001wa5eDJVZRdcHMu","messageID":"msg_d7ae1ff32001CGDNygm6TbXoKc","sessionID":"ses_2851e3b7cffetDjglBtQhaUd1M","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775883129926,"sessionID":"ses_2851e3b7cffetDjglBtQhaUd1M","part":{"id":"prt_d7ae211f40014hl5zi50aVQrAk","messageID":"msg_d7ae1ff32001CGDNygm6TbXoKc","sessionID":"ses_2851e3b7cffetDjglBtQhaUd1M","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-f48861f6988d42cda4e70c98f1f1733b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-032/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-032/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-032 — Dockerfile 多阶段构建 (3 images) Delta Specification\n2: \n3: ## AR Metadata\n4: - **AR ID**: AR-032\n5: - **Title**: Dockerfile 多阶段构建 (3 images)\n6: - **Module**: docker\n7: - **Language**: Dockerfile\n8: - **Size**: S\n9: - **Status**: Implementation Required\n10: \n11: ## Purpose\n12: \n13: This delta specification provides comprehensive acceptance criteria for Dockerfile multi-stage builds with 3 images in the AgentCube project. It defines requirements for building AgentCube components using multi-stage Docker builds to optimize image size, build time, and security. The specification covers three distinct stages: builder, dependency, and runtime stages, with detailed GIVEN/WHEN/THEN scenarios to ensure proper implementation of the multi-stage build pattern.\n14: \n15: ## Requirements\n16: \n17: ### Requirement: Multi-stage build structure with three stages\n18: \n19: The system SHALL implement Dockerfile multi-stage builds with three distinct stages: builder, dependency, and runtime.\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: Dockerfile defines three FROM statements\n22: - **GIVEN** a Dockerfile for an AgentCube component\n23: - **WHEN** the Dockerfile is examined\n24: - **THEN** it SHALL contain exactly three FROM statements\n25: - **AND** the first FROM SHALL define the builder stage\n26: - **AND** the second FROM SHALL define the dependency stage\n27: - **AND** the third FROM SHALL define the runtime stage\n28: \n29: #### Scenario: Builder stage uses build tools\n30: - **GIVEN** the builder stage FROM statement\n31: - **WHEN** the builder stage is defined\n32: - **THEN** it SHALL use an image with build tools (e.g., golang:1.21, node:18, python:3.11)\n33: - **AND** it SHALL include necessary build dependencies\n34: - **AND** it SHALL be named with AS builder\n35: \n36: #### Scenario: Dependency stage extracts runtime dependencies\n37: - **GIVEN** the dependency stage FROM statement\n38: - **WHEN** the dependency stage is defined\n39: - **THEN** it SHALL copy artifacts from the builder stage\n40: - **AND** it SHALL extract only runtime dependencies\n41: - **AND** it SHALL be named with AS dependencies\n42: - **AND** it SHALL use a minimal base image (e.g., debian:bookworm-slim, alpine:3.18)\n43: \n44: #### Scenario: Runtime stage uses minimal base image\n45: - **GIVEN** the runtime stage FROM statement\n46: - **WHEN** the runtime stage is defined\n47: - **THEN** it SHALL use a minimal base image (e.g., distroless, alpine, scratch)\n48: - **AND** it SHALL copy only necessary artifacts from dependency stage\n49: - **AND** it SHALL NOT include build tools or development dependencies\n50: - **AND** it SHALL be the final stage (no AS name required)\n51: \n52: ### Requirement: Build artifacts transfer between stages\n53: \n54: The system SHALL properly transfer build artifacts between the three stages using COPY --from.\n55: \n56: #### Scenario: COPY --from builder to dependencies\n57: - **GIVEN** the dependency stage\n58: - **WHEN** copying artifacts from the builder stage\n59: - **THEN** COPY --from=builder SHALL be used\n60: - **AND** only compiled binaries or packaged artifacts SHALL be copied\n61: - **AND** build artifacts SHALL be copied to appropriate locations (e.g., /app, /usr/local/bin)\n62: \n63: #### Scenario: COPY --from dependencies to runtime\n64: - **GIVEN** the runtime stage\n65: - **WHEN** copying artifacts from the dependency stage\n66: - **THEN** COPY --from=dependencies SHALL be used\n67: - **AND** only runtime dependencies and executables SHALL be copied\n68: - **AND** source artifacts (e.g., source code, build cache) SHALL NOT be copied\n69: \n70: #### Scenario: Dependency isolation in intermediate stage\n71: - **GIVEN** the dependency stage\n72: - **WHEN** processing dependencies\n73: - **THEN** the stage SHALL install and configure runtime dependencies\n74: - **AND** the stage SHALL NOT include source code\n75: - **AND** the stage SHALL prepare the final dependency structure for the runtime stage\n76: \n77: ### Requirement: Layer optimization and caching\n78: \n79: The system SHALL optimize Docker layer usage and leverage build cache effectively.\n80: \n81: #### Scenario: Dockerfile instructions are ordered for caching\n82: - **GIVEN** the Dockerfile structure\n83: - **WHEN** examining instruction order\n84: - **THEN** frequently changing instructions (e.g., COPY source code) SHALL appear later\n85: - **AND** stable instructions (e.g., RUN apt-get install) SHALL appear earlier\n86: - **AND** dependency installation SHALL be grouped into single RUN instructions\n87: \n88: #### Scenario: COPY of dependencies before source code\n89: - **GIVEN** the builder stage\n90: - **WHEN** copying files\n91: - **THEN** dependency manifests (package.json, go.mod, requirements.txt) SHALL be copied first\n92: - **AND** dependency installation SHALL run before copying source code\n93: - **AND** source code SHALL be copied after dependencies are installed\n94: \n95: #### Scenario: Multi-line RUN instructions are combined\n96: - **GIVEN** the Dockerfile\n97: - **WHEN** multiple related commands are needed\n98: - **THEN** commands SHALL be combined using && or \\\n99: - **AND** package installation and cleanup SHALL be in single RUN layer\n100: - **AND** intermediate build artifacts SHALL be cleaned up in same layer\n101: \n102: ### Requirement: Image size optimization\n103: \n104: The system SHALL produce minimal final images through effective multi-stage build usage.\n105: \n106: #### Scenario: Runtime image excludes build tools\n107: - **GIVEN** the final runtime image\n108: - **WHEN** inspecting the image\n109: - **THEN** build tools (gcc, go, node, python-dev) SHALL NOT be present\n110: - **AND** development dependencies SHALL NOT be present\n111: - **AND** build cache files SHALL NOT be present\n112: \n113: #### Scenario: Runtime image includes only necessary files\n114: - **GIVEN** the final runtime image\n115: - **WHEN** examining image contents\n116: - **THEN** only executable binaries SHALL be present\n117: - **AND** only runtime libraries SHALL be present\n118: - **AND** only configuration files SHALL be present\n119: - **AND** source code SHALL NOT be present\n120: \n121: #### Scenario: Multi-stage reduces final image size\n122: - **GIVEN** comparison between single-stage and multi-stage builds\n123: - **WHEN** measuring final image sizes\n124: - **THEN** the multi-stage build SHALL produce a smaller image\n125: - **AND** the size reduction SHALL be significant (at least 50% smaller than single-stage)\n126: - **AND** the builder and dependency stages SHALL not be included in final image\n127: \n128: ### Requirement: Security hardening in multi-stage builds\n129: \n130: The system SHALL implement security best practices through multi-stage build structure.\n131: \n132: #### Scenario: Runtime image uses distroless or minimal base\n133: - **GIVEN** the runtime stage base image\n134: - **WHEN** examining the base image\n135: - **THEN** the base image SHALL be distroless or minimal (e.g., alpine, scratch)\n136: - **AND** the base image SHALL NOT include package managers (apt, apk, yum)\n137: - **AND** the base image SHALL have minimal attack surface\n138: \n139: #### Scenario: Non-root user configuration\n140: - **GIVEN** the runtime stage\n141: - **WHEN** configuring the container user\n142: - **THEN** a non-root user SHALL be created with USER instruction\n143: - **AND** the non-root user SHALL be used to run the application\n144: - **AND** files SHALL be owned by the non-root user with appropriate permissions\n145: \n146: #### Scenario: Security context configuration\n147: - **GIVEN** the Dockerfile\n148: - **WHEN** examining security configurations\n149: - **THEN** file permissions SHALL be restrictive (e.g., 755, 644)\n150: - **AND** sensitive files SHALL NOT be included in image\n151: - **AND** no secrets or credentials SHALL be embedded in the image\n152: \n153: ### Requirement: Component-specific multi-stage builds\n154: \n155: The system SHALL implement appropriate multi-stage builds for each AgentCube component.\n156: \n157: #### Scenario: Controller Manager multi-stage build\n158: - **GIVEN** the Controller Manager Dockerfile\n159: - **WHEN** the build is executed\n160: - **THEN** the builder stage SHALL use golang:1.21\n161: - **AND** the dependency stage SHALL extract Go runtime dependencies\n162: - **AND** the runtime stage SHALL use gcr.io/distroless/static-debian11\n163: - **AND** the final image SHALL contain only the compiled binary\n164: \n165: #### Scenario: Workload Manager multi-stage build\n166: - **GIVEN** the Workload Manager Dockerfile\n167: - **WHEN** the build is executed\n168: - **THEN** the builder stage SHALL use golang:1.21\n169: - **AND** the dependency stage SHALL extract Go runtime dependencies\n170: - **AND** the runtime stage SHALL use gcr.io/distroless/static-debian11\n171: - **AND** the final image SHALL contain only the compiled binary\n172: \n173: #### Scenario: Router multi-stage build\n174: - **GIVEN** the Router Dockerfile\n175: - **WHEN** the build is executed\n176: - **THEN** the builder stage SHALL use golang:1.21\n177: - **AND** the dependency stage SHALL extract Go runtime dependencies\n178: - **AND** the runtime stage SHALL use gcr.io/distroless/static-debian11\n179: - **AND** the final image SHALL contain only the compiled binary\n180: \n181: #### Scenario: Component build consistency\n182: - **GIVEN** all AgentCube component Dockerfiles\n183: - **WHEN** comparing the Dockerfile structures\n184: - **THEN** all components SHALL use the same multi-stage pattern\n185: - **AND** all components SHALL use the same Go version\n186: - **AND** all components SHALL use the same runtime base image\n187: \n188: ### Requirement: Build arguments and versioning\n189: \n190: The system SHALL support build arguments for version control and customization.\n191: \n192: #### Scenario: Build arguments for Go version\n193: - **GIVEN** the Dockerfile\n194: - **WHEN** ARG instructions are used\n195: - **THEN** GO_VERSION SHALL be defined as an ARG\n196: - **AND** GO_VERSION SHALL have a default value (e.g., 1.21)\n197: - **AND** GO_VERSION SHALL be used in FROM statements\n198: \n199: #### Scenario: Build arguments for component version\n200: - **GIVEN** the Dockerfile\n201: - **WHEN** ARG instructions are used\n202: - **THEN** COMPONENT_VERSION SHALL be defined as an ARG\n203: - **AND** COMPONENT_VERSION SHALL be used for labeling\n204: - **AND** COMPONENT_VERSION SHALL be used for version-specific build steps\n205: \n206: #### Scenario: Labels for image metadata\n207: - **GIVEN** the Dockerfile\n208: - **WHEN** LABEL instructions are present\n209: - **THEN** maintainer label SHALL be set\n210: - **AND** version label SHALL be set\n211: - **AND** description label SHALL be set\n212: - **AND** labels SHALL be consistent across components\n213: \n214: ### Requirement: Health and readiness checks\n215: \n216: The system SHALL include health and readiness checks in the runtime stage.\n217: \n218: #### Scenario: Health check endpoint configuration\n219: - **GIVEN** the runtime stage\n220: - **WHEN** HEALTHCHECK instruction is present\n221: - **THEN** HEALTHCHECK SHALL be configured\n222: - **AND** health check interval SHALL be specified (e.g., --interval=30s)\n223: - **AND** health check timeout SHALL be specified (e.g., --timeout=3s)\n224: - **AND** health check retries SHALL be specified (e.g., --retries=3)\n225: \n226: #### Scenario: Health check command uses appropriate protocol\n227: - **GIVEN** the HEALTHCHECK instruction\n228: - **WHEN** examining the health check command\n229: - **THEN** the command SHALL use curl or wget (if available)\n230: - **OR** the command SHALL use a built-in health endpoint\n231: - **AND** the command SHALL check the component's health endpoint (e.g., /healthz, /health)\n232: \n233: ### Requirement: Multi-platform build support\n234: \n235: The system SHALL support multi-platform builds through appropriate base image selection.\n236: \n237: #### Scenario: Base images support multiple architectures\n238: - **GIVEN** the Dockerfile\n239: - **WHEN** selecting base images\n240: - **THEN** builder stage base image SHALL support multi-arch (e.g., golang:1.21)\n241: - **AND** dependency stage base image SHALL support multi-arch (e.g., debian:bookworm-slim)\n242: - **AND** runtime stage base image SHALL support multi-arch (e.g., distroless)\n243: - **AND** images SHALL be buildable for linux/amd64 and linux/arm64\n244: \n245: #### Scenario: Cross-compilation in builder stage\n246: - **GIVEN** the builder stage\n247: - **WHEN** building for different architectures\n248: - **THEN** the build process SHALL support cross-compilation\n249: - **AND** GOARCH and GOOS environment variables SHALL be respected\n250: - **AND** the binary SHALL be compiled for the target architecture\n251: \n252: ### Requirement: Build context and .dockerignore\n253: \n254: The system SHALL optimize build context using .dockerignore file.\n255: \n256: #### Scenario: .dockerignore excludes unnecessary files\n257: - **GIVEN** the .dockerignore file\n258: - **WHEN** examining its contents\n259: - **THEN** .git/ directory SHALL be excluded\n260: - **AND** README.md SHALL be excluded\n261: - **AND** *.md files SHALL be excluded\n262: - **AND** test files SHALL be excluded (e.g., *_test.go)\n263: - **AND** .dockerignore file SHALL be excluded\n264: \n265: #### Scenario: Build context is minimal\n266: - **GIVEN** the Docker build command\n267: - **WHEN** the build context is analyzed\n268: - **THEN** only necessary files SHALL be included in build context\n269: - **AND** large unnecessary files SHALL be excluded via .dockerignore\n270: - **AND** build context size SHALL be minimized\n271: \n272: ### Requirement: Entrypoint and command configuration\n273: \n274: The system SHALL properly configure entrypoint and command in the runtime stage.\n275: \n276: #### Scenario: Entrypoint uses the compiled binary\n277: - **GIVEN** the runtime stage\n278: - **WHEN** ENTRYPOINT instruction is set\n279: - **THEN** ENTRYPOINT SHALL point to the compiled binary\n280: - **AND** the binary path SHALL be absolute (e.g., /app/controller-manager)\n281: - **AND** the binary SHALL be executable\n282: \n283: #### Scenario: CMD supports default arguments\n284: - **GIVEN** the runtime stage\n285: - **WHEN** CMD instruction is set\n286: - **THEN** CMD SHALL provide default arguments\n287: - **AND** default arguments SHALL be sensible for the component\n288: - **AND** CMD arguments can be overridden at runtime\n289: \n290: #### Scenario: Entrypoint script for initialization (optional)\n291: - **GIVEN** the runtime stage with an entrypoint script\n292: - **WHEN** an entrypoint script is used\n293: - **THEN** the script SHALL be copied from dependency stage\n294: - **AND** the script SHALL be executable\n295: - **AND** the script SHALL perform necessary initialization\n296: - **AND** the script SHALL exec the main binary at the end\n297: \n298: ### Requirement: Cache and volume configuration\n299: \n300: The system SHALL configure appropriate cache mounts and volumes for build optimization.\n301: \n302: #### Scenario: Build cache for Go modules\n303: - **GIVEN** the builder stage\n304: - **WHEN** building Go dependencies\n305: - **THEN** --mount=type=cache,target=/go/pkg/mod SHALL be used for go mod download\n306: - **AND** build cache SHALL persist across builds\n307: - **AND** dependency download time SHALL be reduced\n308: \n309: #### Scenario: Build cache for Go build\n310: - **GIVEN** the builder stage\n311: - **WHEN** building the Go binary\n312: - **THEN** --mount=type=cache,target=/root/.cache/go-build SHALL be used for go build\n313: - **AND** incremental builds SHALL be faster\n314: - **AND** compiled object files SHALL be cached\n315: \n316: ### Requirement: Reproducible builds\n317: \n318: The system SHALL support reproducible builds through proper Dockerfile practices.\n319: \n320: #### Scenario: Fixed versions in base images\n321: - **GIVEN** the Dockerfile\n322: - **WHEN** specifying base images\n323: - **THEN** base images SHALL use specific tags (e.g., golang:1.21.5)\n324: - **OR** base images SHALL use digests for complete reproducibility\n325: - **AND** latest tag SHALL NOT be used\n326: \n327: #### Scenario: Deterministic build process\n328: - **GIVEN** the Dockerfile\n329: - **WHEN** examining build instructions\n330: - **THEN** time and random factors SHALL be minimized\n331: - **AND** build timestamps SHALL be normalized if possible\n332: - **AND** the build SHALL produce identical outputs given same inputs\n333: \n334: ### Requirement: Documentation and comments\n335: \n336: The system SHALL provide clear documentation within the Dockerfile.\n337: \n338: #### Scenario: Dockerfile has descriptive comments\n339: - **GIVEN** the Dockerfile\n340: - **WHEN** examining comments\n341: - **THEN** each stage SHALL have a comment describing its purpose\n342: - **AND** complex build steps SHALL have explanatory comments\n343: - **AND** non-obvious COPY commands SHALL have comments\n344: \n345: #### Scenario: Dockerfile follows best practices\n346: - **GIVEN** the Dockerfile\n347: - **WHEN** reviewing against Dockerfile best practices\n348: - **THEN** .dockerignore SHALL be present\n349: - **AND** instructions SHALL be ordered for optimal caching\n350: - **AND** layers SHALL be minimized\n351: - **AND** multi-stage build SHALL be used effectively\n352: - **AND** security best practices SHALL be followed\n353: \n354: ---\n355: \n356: ## Backward Compatibility\n357: \n358: This delta specification defines multi-stage Dockerfile builds for the AgentCube project. The multi-stage builds are an optimization over existing single-stage builds and produce the same runtime images with improved efficiency and security. The final runtime images maintain compatibility with existing deployments, as they contain the same binaries and dependencies.\n359: \n360: ## Dependencies\n361: \n362: This delta specification depends on:\n363: - Docker 20.10+ (for multi-stage build support)\n364: - Go 1.21+ (for building AgentCube components)\n365: - Base design document: `design.md`\n366: - Base specification document: `deployment/spec.md`\n367: - AR: AR-030 — Helm Chart 模板与 Values (for image configuration)\n368: \n369: ## Breaking Changes\n370: \n371: None. This delta specification defines an optimized build process using multi-stage Docker builds. The final runtime images remain compatible with existing deployments, and the build process change does not affect runtime behavior or API compatibility.\n372: \n373: ## Security Considerations\n374: \n375: 1. **Minimal Runtime Images**: Using distroless or minimal base images reduces the attack surface by excluding package managers, shells, and unnecessary tools.\n376: 2. **No Secrets in Images**: Multi-stage builds ensure no secrets or credentials are embedded in the final image, as secrets are only used in the builder stage and never copied to runtime.\n377: 3. **Non-Root Execution**: The runtime stage runs as a non-root user, reducing the impact of container escape vulnerabilities.\n378: 4. **Limited Permissions**: File permissions are restrictive, and the container has minimal privileges.\n379: 5. **Reproducible Builds**: Using specific image versions and digests ensures reproducible, verifiable builds.\n380: 6. **Build Isolation**: The builder and dependency stages are not included in the final image, isolating build-time dependencies.\n381: 7. **CVE Scanning**: Minimal images are easier to scan for vulnerabilities and have fewer CVEs to manage.\n382: \n383: ## Testing Strategy\n384: \n385: ### Build Tests\n386: - Verify multi-stage builds complete successfully for all components\n387: - Verify build artifacts are correctly transferred between stages\n388: - Verify final images contain only necessary files\n389: - Verify build cache improves incremental build times\n390: \n391: ### Image Size Tests\n392: - Measure final image size for each component\n393: - Compare with single-stage build size\n394: - Verify size reduction meets expectations (>50% reduction)\n395: - Verify builder and dependency stages are not in final image\n396: \n397: ### Security Tests\n398: - Scan final images for CVEs using tools like Trivy or Snyk\n399: - Verify runtime images use distroless or minimal base\n400: - Verify no build tools are present in runtime images\n401: - Verify non-root user is configured correctly\n402: - Verify no secrets or credentials in final image\n403: \n404: ### Functional Tests\n405: - Run containers built with multi-stage Dockerfiles\n406: - Verify containers start and run correctly\n407: - Verify health checks work as expected\n408: - Verify components can communicate with each other\n409: - Verify all functionality works as expected\n410: \n411: ### Multi-Platform Tests\n412: - Build images for linux/amd64\n413: - Build images for linux/arm64\n414: - Verify images run correctly on both architectures\n415: - Verify cross-compilation works correctly\n416: \n417: ### Cache Tests\n418: - Verify Go module cache works correctly\n419: - Verify Go build cache works correctly\n420: - Measure cache hit/miss rates\n421: - Verify incremental builds are faster\n422: \n423: ### Reproducibility Tests\n424: - Build the same image twice and compare\n425: - Verify images are identical using digests\n426: - Verify build output is deterministic\n427: - Verify using image tags and digests produces reproducible results\n428: \n429: ### Integration Tests\n430: - Test multi-stage builds in CI/CD pipeline\n431: - Verify builds work with Docker BuildKit\n432: - Verify builds work with Buildah (if applicable)\n433: - Verify image signing and verification (if implemented)\n\n(End of file - total 433 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-032 — Dockerfile 多阶段构建 (3 images) Delta Specification\n\n## AR Metadata\n- **AR ID**: AR-032\n- **Title**: Dockerfile 多阶段构建 (3 images)\n- **Module**: docker\n- **Language**: Dockerfile\n- **Size**: S\n- **Status**: Implementation Required\n\n## Purpose\n\nThis delta specification provides comprehensive acceptance criteria for Dockerfile multi-stage builds with 3 images in the AgentCube project. It defines requirements for building AgentCube components using multi-stage Docker builds to optimize image size, build time, and security. The specification covers three distinct stages: builder, dependency, and runtime stages, with detailed GIVEN/WHEN/THEN scenarios to ensure proper implementation of the multi-stage build pattern.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: Multi-stage build structure with three stages\n\nThe system SHALL implement Dockerfile multi-stage builds with three distinct stages: builder, dependency, and runtime.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-032/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775883129905,"end":1775883129924}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775883129930,"sessionID":"ses_2851e3b7cffetDjglBtQhaUd1M","part":{"id":"prt_d7ae21411001r6i0vvzMIXCzMp","messageID":"msg_d7ae1ff32001CGDNygm6TbXoKc","sessionID":"ses_2851e3b7cffetDjglBtQhaUd1M","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-927110b4247e41bd8f91ebaeab144338","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-032/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-032/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-032: Dockerfile 多阶段构建 — Design Document\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This design document outlines the technical implementation of a multi-stage Dockerfile build strategy for the AgentCube project. The implementation uses three independent build stages to create optimized production images, significantly reducing image size, improving build efficiency, enhancing security, and providing flexible image variants for different use cases.\n6: \n7: **Module:** `docker`  \n8: **Language:** Dockerfile  \n9: **Source Root:** `/changes/AR-032/`  \n10: **Size:** S\n11: \n12: ## Architecture\n13: \n14: ### Multi-Stage Build Architecture\n15: \n16: The implementation follows a three-stage build architecture:\n17: \n18: ```\n19: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n20: │                     Build Pipeline                          │\n21: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n22: │                                                              │\n23: │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n24: │  │           Stage 1: Builder                            │  │\n25: │  │  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │  │\n26: │  │  │ • golang:1.21-alpine base image               │  │  │\n27: │  │  │ • Install build tools (gcc, musl-dev)        │  │  │\n28: │  │  │ • Download Go dependencies (go.mod/go.sum)   │  │  │\n29: │  │  │ • Copy source code                           │  │  │\n30: │  │  │ • Compile agentd binary                      │  │  │\n31: │  │  │ • Install Python dependencies                 │  │  │\n32: │  │  │ • Prepare picod environment                   │  │  │\n33: │  │  └────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │  │\n34: │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n35: │                           │                                  │\n36: │                           ▼                                  │\n37: │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n38: │  │           Stage 2: Verifier (Optional)                │  │\n39: │  │  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │  │\n40: │  │  │ • Inherit from builder                        │  │  │\n41: │  │  │ • Run Go unit tests                           │  │  │\n42: │  │  │ • Run Python unit tests                       │  │  │\n43: │  │  │ • Execute code quality checks                 │  │  │\n44: │  │  │ • Verify build artifacts                      │  │  │\n45: │  │  │ • Generate test reports                       │  │  │\n46: │  │  └────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │  │\n47: │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n48: │                           │                                  │\n49: │                           ▼                                  │\n50: │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n51: │  │           Stage 3: Runtime                            │  │\n52: │  │  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │  │\n53: │  │  │ • alpine:3.19 minimal base image              │  │  │\n54: │  │  │ • Install runtime deps only (ca-certificates) │  │  │\n55: │  │  │ • Create non-privileged user (agentcube:1000) │  │  │\n56: │  │  │ • Copy compiled agentd binary                 │  │  │\n57: │  │  │ • Copy Python site-packages                  │  │  │\n58: │  │  │ • Copy picod source code                      │  │  │\n59: │  │  │ • Configure health check                      │  │  │\n60: │  │  │ • Set security context                        │  │  │\n61: │  │  └────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │  │\n62: │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n63: │                                                              │\n64: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n65: ```\n66: \n67: ### Image Variants\n68: \n69: The implementation provides three image variants for different use cases:\n70: \n71: | Variant | Target Stage | Tag | Use Case |\n72: |---------|--------------|-----|----------|\n73: | Production | Runtime | `:latest`, `:vX.Y.Z` | Production deployments |\n74: | Development | Builder | `:dev` | Debugging and development |\n75: | Test | Verifier | `:test` | Running test suites |\n76: \n77: ### Build Flow\n78: \n79: ```mermaid\n80: graph TD\n81:     A[Source Code] --> B[Builder Stage]\n82:     B --> C[Compile agentd]\n83:     B --> D[Install Python deps]\n84:     C --> E[Optional: Verifier Stage]\n85:     D --> E\n86:     E --> F[Run Tests]\n87:     F --> G[Runtime Stage]\n88:     G --> H[Copy artifacts]\n89:     H --> I[Configure security]\n90:     I --> J[Production Image]\n91:     \n92:     B -.-> K[Development Image]\n93:     E -.-> L[Test Image]\n94: ```\n95: \n96: ## Data Structures\n97: \n98: ### Dockerfile Structure\n99: \n100: ```dockerfile\n101: # ============================================\n102: # Build Arguments\n103: # ============================================\n104: ARG GO_VERSION=1.21\n105: ARG ALPINE_VERSION=3.19\n106: ARG BUILD_VERSION=dev\n107: ARG BUILD_TIME\n108: ARG GIT_COMMIT\n109: \n110: # ============================================\n111: # Stage 1: Builder\n112: # ============================================\n113: FROM golang:${GO_VERSION}-alpine AS builder\n114: \n115: # Build metadata\n116: ARG BUILD_VERSION\n117: ARG BUILD_TIME\n118: ARG GIT_COMMIT\n119: \n120: # Install build tools\n121: RUN apk add --no-cache \\\n122:     python3 \\\n123:     py3-pip \\\n124:     gcc \\\n125:     musl-dev \\\n126:     git\n127: \n128: # Set working directory\n129: WORKDIR /build\n130: \n131: # Go dependency optimization - download first for caching\n132: COPY go.mod go.sum ./\n133: RUN go mod download\n134: \n135: # Copy Go source code\n136: COPY ./pkg ./pkg\n137: COPY ./cmd ./cmd\n138: \n139: # Build agentd with embedded version info\n140: RUN CGO_ENABLED=0 GOOS=linux go build \\\n141:     -ldflags=\"-s -w -X main.Version=${BUILD_VERSION} -X main.BuildTime=${BUILD_TIME} -X main.GitCommit=${GIT_COMMIT}\" \\\n142:     -o agentd \\\n143:     ./cmd/agentd\n144: \n145: # Copy Python source and dependencies\n146: COPY ./cmd/picod /build/picod\n147: COPY requirements.txt ./\n148: RUN pip install --no-cache-dir -r requirements.txt\n149: \n150: # ============================================\n151: # Stage 2: Verifier (Optional)\n152: # ============================================\n153: FROM builder AS verifier\n154: \n155: # Run Go tests\n156: RUN go test ./... -v -coverprofile=coverage.out\n157: \n158: # Run Python tests\n159: RUN pytest /build/picod/tests -v\n160: \n161: # Generate test report\n162: RUN go tool cover -html=coverage.out -o coverage.html\n163: \n164: # ============================================\n165: # Stage 3: Runtime\n166: # ============================================\n167: FROM alpine:${ALPINE_VERSION} AS runtime\n168: \n169: # Build metadata\n170: ARG BUILD_VERSION\n171: ARG GIT_COMMIT\n172: \n173: # Labels for image metadata\n174: LABEL maintainer=\"agentcube@volcano.sh\" \\\n175:       version=\"${BUILD_VERSION}\" \\\n176:       git.commit=\"${GIT_COMMIT}\" \\\n177:       description=\"AgentCube Runtime Image\"\n178: \n179: # Install runtime dependencies only\n180: RUN apk add --no-cache \\\n181:     ca-certificates \\\n182:     python3 \\\n183:     py3-pip \\\n184:     tzdata \\\n185:     && update-ca-certificates\n186: \n187: # Create non-privileged user\n188: RUN addgroup -g 1000 agentcube && \\\n189:     adduser -D -u 1000 -G agentcube agentcube\n190: \n191: # Set working directory\n192: WORKDIR /app\n193: \n194: # Copy compiled binaries from builder\n195: COPY --from=builder /build/agentd /app/agentd\n196: \n197: # Copy Python environment\n198: COPY --from=builder /usr/local/lib/python3.11/site-packages /usr/local/lib/python3.11/site-packages\n199: COPY --from=builder /build/picod /app/picod\n200: \n201: # Set ownership\n202: RUN chown -R agentcube:agentcube /app\n203: \n204: # Switch to non-privileged user\n205: USER agentcube\n206: \n207: # Expose ports\n208: EXPOSE 8080 9090\n209: \n210: # Health check\n211: HEALTHCHECK --interval=30s --timeout=10s --start-period=5s --retries=3 \\\n212:     CMD agentd health || exit 1\n213: \n214: # Entry point\n215: ENTRYPOINT [\"/app/agentd\"]\n216: ```\n217: \n218: ### Build Arguments Schema\n219: \n220: | Argument | Default | Description | Usage |\n221: |----------|---------|-------------|-------|\n222: | `GO_VERSION` | `1.21` | Go compiler version | Controls base Go image |\n223: | `ALPINE_VERSION` | `3.19` | Alpine Linux version | Controls base runtime image |\n224: | `BUILD_VERSION` | `dev` | Application version | Embedded in binary metadata |\n225: | `BUILD_TIME` | (auto) | Build timestamp | Embedded in binary metadata |\n226: | `GIT_COMMIT` | (auto) | Git commit hash | Embedded in binary metadata |\n227: \n228: ### Environment Variables Schema\n229: \n230: | Variable | Default | Description |\n231: |----------|---------|-------------|\n232: | `AGENTCUBE_ENV` | `production` | Runtime environment |\n233: | `AGENTCUBE_LOG_LEVEL` | `info` | Logging level |\n234: | `AGENTCUBE_LOG_FORMAT` | `json` | Log format (json/text) |\n235: | `AGENTCUBE_PORT` | `8080` | Service port |\n236: | `AGENTCUBE_METRICS_ENABLED` | `true` | Enable metrics endpoint |\n237: | `AGENTCUBE_METRICS_PORT` | `9090` | Metrics port |\n238: \n239: ### .dockerignore Patterns\n240: \n241: ```dockerignore\n242: # Git files\n243: .git\n244: .gitignore\n245: .gitattributes\n246: \n247: # Documentation\n248: *.md\n249: docs/\n250: \n251: # Development files\n252: .vscode/\n253: .idea/\n254: *.swp\n255: *.swo\n256: \n257: # Build artifacts\n258: dist/\n259: build/\n260: *.exe\n261: *.dll\n262: *.dylib\n263: \n264: # Test files\n265: *_test.go\n266: pytest.ini\n267: .coverage\n268: .coverage.*\n269: \n270: # CI/CD\n271: .github/\n272: .gitlab-ci.yml\n273: .travis.yml\n274: \n275: # IDE\n276: .vscode/\n277: .idea/\n278: \n279: # OS\n280: .DS_Store\n281: Thumbs.db\n282: \n283: # Temporary files\n284: tmp/\n285: temp/\n286: *.tmp\n287: \n288: # Docker files (except Dockerfile)\n289: docker-compose*.yml\n290: *.dockerfile\n291: ```\n292: \n293: ## API Contracts\n294: \n295: ### Build Commands\n296: \n297: #### Single Architecture Build\n298: \n299: ```bash\n300: # Build production image\n301: docker build \\\n302:   --build-arg GO_VERSION=1.21 \\\n303:   --build-arg BUILD_VERSION=v1.0.0 \\\n304:   --build-arg BUILD_TIME=$(date -u +%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%SZ) \\\n305:   --build-arg GIT_COMMIT=$(git rev-parse --short HEAD) \\\n306:   -t agentcube:latest \\\n307:   -t agentcube:v1.0.0 \\\n308:   .\n309: \n310: # Build development image\n311: docker build \\\n312:   --target builder \\\n313:   -t agentcube:dev \\\n314:   .\n315: \n316: # Build test image\n317: docker build \\\n318:   --target verifier \\\n319:   -t agentcube:test \\\n320:   .\n321: ```\n322: \n323: #### Multi-Architecture Build\n324: \n325: ```bash\n326: # Create and use buildx builder\n327: docker buildx create --name agentcube-builder --use\n328: \n329: # Build and push multi-arch images\n330: docker buildx build \\\n331:   --platform linux/amd64,linux/arm64 \\\n332:   --build-arg GO_VERSION=1.21 \\\n333:   --build-arg BUILD_VERSION=v1.0.0 \\\n334:   --build-arg BUILD_TIME=$(date -u +%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%SZ) \\\n335:   --build-arg GIT_COMMIT=$(git rev-parse --short HEAD) \\\n336:   -t registry.example.com/agentcube:latest \\\n337:   -t registry.example.com/agentcube:v1.0.0 \\\n338:   --push \\\n339:   .\n340: \n341: # Build multi-arch images locally\n342: docker buildx build \\\n343:   --platform linux/amd64,linux/arm64 \\\n344:   -t agentcube:multiarch \\\n345:   --load \\\n346:   .\n347: ```\n348: \n349: ### Runtime API\n350: \n351: #### Container Entry Points\n352: \n353: | Stage | Entry Point | Default Command |\n354: |-------|-------------|-----------------|\n355: | Builder | `/bin/sh` | Interactive shell |\n356: | Verifier | `/bin/sh` | Test execution scripts |\n357: | Runtime | `/app/agentd` | Start agentd daemon |\n358: \n359: #### Health Check Endpoint\n360: \n361: ```\n362: GET /healthz\n363: Response: 200 OK (healthy) or 503 Service Unavailable (unhealthy)\n364: ```\n365: \n366: #### Metrics Endpoint\n367: \n368: ```\n369: GET /metrics\n370: Response: Prometheus metrics format\n371: ```\n372: \n373: ### Build Output Schema\n374: \n375: #### Image Layer Information\n376: \n377: ```bash\n378: docker history agentcube:latest\n379: ```\n380: \n381: Output structure:\n382: ```\n383: IMAGE           CREATED         CREATED BY                                      SIZE\n384: <runtime-id>    <timestamp>     /bin/sh -c #(nop) CMD [\"/app/agentd\"]          0B\n385: <runtime-id>    <timestamp>     /bin/sh -c #(nop) HEALTHCHECK...                0B\n386: <runtime-id>    <timestamp>     /bin/sh -c #(nop) EXPOSE 8080 9090              0B\n387: <runtime-id>    <timestamp>     /bin/sh -c #(nop) USER agentcube                0B\n388: <runtime-id>    <timestamp>     /bin/sh -c chown -R agentcube:agentcube /app    1.2MB\n389: <runtime-id>    <timestamp>     /bin/sh -c #(nop) COPY dir:... in /app/picod    5.5MB\n390: <runtime-id>    <timestamp>     /bin/sh -c #(nop) COPY dir:... in /usr/local   85MB\n391: <runtime-id>    <timestamp>     /bin/sh -c #(nop) COPY file:... in /app/agentd  15MB\n392: <runtime-id>    <timestamp>     /bin/sh -c apk add --no-cache ca-certificates... 12MB\n393: <runtime-id>    <timestamp>     /bin/sh -c addgroup -g 1000 agentcube && ...    1.5KB\n394: <runtime-id>    <timestamp>     /bin/sh -c #(nop) WORKDIR /app                   0B\n395: <runtime-id>    <timestamp>     <base-image-id>                                  7.5MB\n396: ```\n397: \n398: #### Image Size Analysis\n399: \n400: ```bash\n401: docker images agentcube:latest --format \"{{.Size}}\"\n402: ```\n403: \n404: Expected output:\n405: - **Production Image**: ~150-250 MB\n406: - **Builder Image**: ~800-1200 MB\n407: - **Verifier Image**: ~850-1250 MB\n408: \n409: ## Error Handling\n410: \n411: ### Build Time Errors\n412: \n413: #### Dockerfile Syntax Errors\n414: \n415: **Detection:**\n416: ```bash\n417: docker build --check .\n418: ```\n419: \n420: **Common Errors:**\n421: \n422: | Error | Cause | Resolution |\n423: |-------|-------|------------|\n424: | `unknown instruction` | Invalid Dockerfile syntax | Verify Dockerfile syntax and Docker version |\n425: | `failed to compute cache key` | Missing file or incorrect path | Check COPY paths and file existence |\n426: | `no such file or directory` | Source file not found | Verify file paths and .dockerignore |\n427: | `failed to solve` | Dependency unavailable | Check network connectivity and base image availability |\n428: \n429: #### Build Failures\n430: \n431: **Go Compilation Errors:**\n432: ```\n433: Step X/Y : RUN go build -o agentd ./cmd/agentd\n434:  ---> Running in <container-id>\n435: # github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/cmd/agentd\n436: ./main.go:XX:YY: undefined: Foo\n437: error building image\n438: ```\n439: \n440: **Resolution:**\n441: 1. Check Go code for compilation errors\n442: 2. Verify Go version compatibility\n443: 3. Ensure all dependencies are in go.mod\n444: 4. Check for platform-specific code issues\n445: \n446: **Python Dependency Errors:**\n447: ```\n448: Step X/Y : RUN pip install -r requirements.txt\n449:  ---> Running in <container-id>\n450: ERROR: Could not find a version that satisfies the requirement Foo\n451: error building image\n452: ```\n453: \n454: **Resolution:**\n455: 1. Verify requirements.txt syntax\n456: 2. Check dependency availability in PyPI\n457: 3. Ensure Python version compatibility\n458: 4. Use pinned versions for reproducibility\n459: \n460: ### Runtime Errors\n461: \n462: #### Container Startup Failures\n463: \n464: **Binary Execution Errors:**\n465: ```\n466: standard_init_linux.go:228: exec user process caused: no such file or directory\n467: ```\n468: \n469: **Resolution:**\n470: 1. Verify binary was successfully copied from builder stage\n471: 2. Check binary architecture compatibility\n472: 3. Ensure proper execute permissions\n473: 4. Verify dynamic library dependencies\n474: \n475: **Permission Errors:**\n476: ```\n477: permission denied: trying to connect to the Docker daemon socket\n478: ```\n479: \n480: **Resolution:**\n481: 1. Verify non-privileged user configuration\n482: 2. Check file ownership and permissions\n483: 3. Review security context settings\n484: 4. Ensure proper user/group IDs\n485: \n486: #### Health Check Failures\n487: \n488: **Detection:**\n489: ```bash\n490: docker inspect --format='{{.State.Health.Status}}' <container-id>\n491: ```\n492: \n493: **Common Causes:**\n494: - Port not exposed or bound\n495: - Application not starting properly\n496: - Network configuration issues\n497: - Insufficient resources\n498: \n499: **Resolution:**\n500: 1. Check application logs: `docker logs <container-id>`\n501: 2. Verify port exposure and binding\n502: 3. Review resource limits\n503: 4. Test health endpoint manually\n504: \n505: ### Validation Scripts\n506: \n507: #### Build Validation Script\n508: \n509: ```bash\n510: #!/bin/bash\n511: # scripts/validate-build.sh\n512: \n513: set -e\n514: \n515: echo \"Validating Dockerfile...\"\n516: \n517: # Check syntax\n518: echo \"Checking Dockerfile syntax...\"\n519: docker build --check . || exit 1\n520: \n521: # Check base images\n522: echo \"Verifying base images...\"\n523: docker pull golang:1.21-alpine\n524: docker pull alpine:3.19\n525: \n526: # Build all targets\n527: echo \"Building all targets...\"\n528: docker build --target builder -t agentcube:dev .\n529: docker build --target verifier -t agentcube:test .\n530: docker build -t agentcube:latest .\n531: \n532: # Verify image sizes\n533: echo \"Checking image sizes...\"\n534: DEV_SIZE=$(docker images agentcube:dev --format \"{{.Size}}\")\n535: TEST_SIZE=$(docker images agentcube:test --format \"{{.Size}}\"))\n536: PROD_SIZE=$(docker images agentcube:latest --format \"{{.Size}}\")\n537: \n538: echo \"Development image size: $DEV_SIZE\"\n539: echo \"Test image size: $TEST_SIZE\"\n540: echo \"Production image size: $PROD_SIZE\"\n541: \n542: # Check image layers\n543: echo \"Inspecting image layers...\"\n544: docker history agentcube:latest\n545: \n546: echo \"Build validation completed successfully!\"\n547: ```\n548: \n549: #### Runtime Validation Script\n550: \n551: ```bash\n552: #!/bin/bash\n553: # scripts/validate-runtime.sh\n554: \n555: set -e\n556: \n557: echo \"Validating runtime container...\"\n558: \n559: # Run container\n560: CONTAINER_ID=$(docker run -d --name agentcube-test agentcube:latest)\n561: \n562: # Wait for startup\n563: sleep 10\n564: \n565: # Check container status\n566: STATUS=$(docker inspect --format='{{.State.Status}}' $CONTAINER_ID)\n567: echo \"Container status: $STATUS\"\n568: \n569: # Check health status\n570: HEALTH=$(docker inspect --format='{{.State.Health.Status}}' $CONTAINER_ID)\n571: echo \"Health status: $HEALTH\"\n572: \n573: # Check logs\n574: echo \"Container logs:\"\n575: docker logs $CONTAINER_ID\n576: \n577: # Test health endpoint\n578: echo \"Testing health endpoint...\"\n579: docker exec $CONTAINER_ID wget -qO- http://localhost:8080/healthz\n580: \n581: # Cleanup\n582: docker stop $CONTAINER_ID\n583: docker rm $CONTAINER_ID\n584: \n585: echo \"Runtime validation completed successfully!\"\n586: ```\n587: \n588: ## Testing Strategy\n589: \n590: ### Unit Tests\n591: \n592: #### Dockerfile Syntax Validation\n593: \n594: ```bash\n595: # Use Hadolint for best practices checking\n596: docker run --rm -i hadolint/hadolint hadolint --ignore DL3008 --ignore DL3018 < Dockerfile\n597: ```\n598: \n599: #### Build Script Tests\n600: \n601: ```bash\n602: #!/bin/bash\n603: # tests/test-build-scripts.sh\n604: \n605: # Test 1: Verify build arguments\n606: test_build_arguments() {\n607:     docker build \\\n608:       --build-arg GO_VERSION=1.21 \\\n609:       --build-arg BUILD_VERSION=test \\\n610:       -t test:args \\\n611:       .\n612:     \n613:     VERSION=$(docker run test:args /app/agentd version | jq -r '.version')\n614:     [ \"$VERSION\" = \"test\" ] || exit 1\n615: }\n616: \n617: # Test 2: Verify non-root user\n618: test_non_root_user() {\n619:     USER=$(docker run --rm agentcube:latest whoami)\n620:     [ \"$USER\" = \"agentcube\" ] || exit 1\n621: }\n622: \n623: # Test 3: Verify binary execution\n624: test_binary_execution() {\n625:     docker run --rm agentcube:latest /app/agentd version\n626: }\n627: ```\n628: \n629: ### Integration Tests\n630: \n631: #### Build Integration Tests\n632: \n633: ```bash\n634: #!/bin/bash\n635: # tests/integration/build-integration.sh\n636: \n637: set -e\n638: \n639: echo \"Running build integration tests...\"\n640: \n641: # Test 1: Full build pipeline\n642: echo \"Test 1: Full build pipeline\"\n643: docker build -t agentcube:integration-test .\n644: \n645: # Test 2: Multi-stage target selection\n646: echo \"Test 2: Multi-stage target selection\"\n647: docker build --target builder -t agentcube:builder-integration .\n648: docker build --target verifier -t agentcube:verifier-integration .\n649: \n650: # Test 3: Layer caching\n651: echo \"Test 3: Layer caching\"\n652: TIME1=$(time docker build -t agentcube:cache-test1 . 2>&1 | grep real)\n653: TIME2=$(time docker build -t agentcube:cache-test2 . 2>&1 | grep real)\n654: echo \"First build: $TIME1\"\n655: echo \"Cached build: $TIME2\"\n656: \n657: # Test 4: Multi-architecture build\n658: echo \"Test 4: Multi-architecture build\"\n659: docker buildx create --use\n660: docker buildx build \\\n661:   --platform linux/amd64 \\\n662:   -t agentcube:amd64-test \\\n663:   --load \\\n664:   .\n665: docker buildx build \\\n666:   --platform linux/arm64 \\\n667:   -t agentcube:arm64-test \\\n668:   --load \\\n669:   .\n670: \n671: echo \"Build integration tests passed!\"\n672: ```\n673: \n674: #### Runtime Integration Tests\n675: \n676: ```bash\n677: #!/bin/bash\n678: # tests/integration/runtime-integration.sh\n679: \n680: set -e\n681: \n682: echo \"Running runtime integration tests...\"\n683: \n684: # Test 1: Container startup\n685: echo \"Test 1: Container startup\"\n686: CONTAINER_ID=$(docker run -d agentcube:latest)\n687: sleep 10\n688: STATUS=$(docker inspect --format='{{.State.Status}}' $CONTAINER_ID)\n689: [ \"$STATUS\" = \"running\" ] || exit 1\n690: docker stop $CONTAINER_ID\n691: \n692: # Test 2: Health check\n693: echo \"Test 2: Health check\"\n694: CONTAINER_ID=$(docker run -d agentcube:latest)\n695: sleep 15\n696: HEALTH=$(docker inspect --format='{{.State.Health.Status}}' $CONTAINER_ID)\n697: [ \"$HEALTH\" = \"healthy\" ] || exit 1\n698: docker stop $CONTAINER_ID\n699: \n700: # Test 3: Port exposure\n701: echo \"Test 3: Port exposure\"\n702: CONTAINER_ID=$(docker run -d -p 8080:8080 agentcube:latest)\n703: sleep 10\n704: curl -f http://localhost:8080/healthz || exit 1\n705: docker stop $CONTAINER_ID\n706: \n707: # Test 4: Resource constraints\n708: echo \"Test 4: Resource constraints\"\n709: CONTAINER_ID=$(docker run -d --memory=\"512m\" --cpus=\"1.0\" agentcube:latest)\n710: sleep 10\n711: STATUS=$(docker inspect --format='{{.State.Status}}' $CONTAINER_ID)\n712: [ \"$STATUS\" = \"running\" ] || exit 1\n713: docker stop $CONTAINER_ID\n714: \n715: echo \"Runtime integration tests passed!\"\n716: ```\n717: \n718: ### Performance Tests\n719: \n720: #### Build Performance Tests\n721: \n722: ```bash\n723: #!/bin/bash\n724: # tests/performance/build-performance.sh\n725: \n726: echo \"Running build performance tests...\"\n727: \n728: # Test 1: Cold build time\n729: echo \"Test 1: Cold build time\"\n730: docker builder prune -af\n731: START=$(date +%s)\n732: docker build -t agentcube:perf-cold .\n733: END=$(date +%s)\n734: echo \"Cold build time: $((END - START)) seconds\"\n735: \n736: # Test 2: Warm build time (with cache)\n737: echo \"Test 2: Warm build time\"\n738: START=$(date +%s)\n739: docker build -t agentcube:perf-warm .\n740: END=$(date +%s)\n741: echo \"Warm build time: $((END - START)) seconds\"\n742: \n743: # Test 3: Image size analysis\n744: echo \"Test 3: Image size analysis\"\n745: docker images agentcube:latest --format \"table {{.Repository}}\\t{{.Tag}}\\t{{.Size}}\"\n746: docker history agentcube:latest\n747: \n748: # Test 4: Layer cache efficiency\n749: echo \"Test 4: Layer cache efficiency\"\n750: docker build --progress=plain -t agentcube:perf-cache . 2>&1 | grep -i \"cache\"\n751: \n752: echo \"Build performance tests completed!\"\n753: ```\n754: \n755: #### Runtime Performance Tests\n756: \n757: ```bash\n758: #!/bin/bash\n759: # tests/performance/runtime-performance.sh\n760: \n761: echo \"Running runtime performance tests...\"\n762: \n763: # Test 1: Startup time\n764: echo \"Test 1: Startup time\"\n765: START=$(date +%s%N)\n766: CONTAINER_ID=$(docker run -d agentcube:latest)\n767: docker logs --follow $CONTAINER_ID &\n768: LOG_PID=$!\n769: while ! docker exec $CONTAINER_ID wget -qO- http://localhost:8080/healthz > /dev/null 2>&1; do\n770:     sleep 0.1\n771: done\n772: END=$(date +%s%N)\n773: kill $LOG_PID 2>/dev/null\n774: STARTUP_TIME=$(( (END - START) / 1000000 ))\n775: echo \"Startup time: ${STARTUP_TIME}ms\"\n776: docker stop $CONTAINER_ID\n777: \n778: # Test 2: Memory usage\n779: echo \"Test 2: Memory usage\"\n780: CONTAINER_ID=$(docker run -d agentcube:latest)\n781: sleep 10\n782: MEMORY=$(docker stats --no-stream --format \"{{.MemUsage}}\" $CONTAINER_ID)\n783: echo \"Memory usage: $MEMORY\"\n784: docker stop $CONTAINER_ID\n785: \n786: # Test 3: CPU usage\n787: echo \"Test 3: CPU usage\"\n788: CONTAINER_ID=$(docker run -d agentcube:latest)\n789: sleep 10\n790: CPU=$(docker stats --no-stream --format \"{{.CPUPerc}}\" $CONTAINER_ID)\n791: echo \"CPU usage: $CPU\"\n792: docker stop $CONTAINER_ID\n793: \n794: echo \"Runtime performance tests completed!\"\n795: ```\n796: \n797: ### Security Tests\n798: \n799: #### Vulnerability Scanning\n800: \n801: ```bash\n802: #!/bin/bash\n803: # tests/security/vulnerability-scan.sh\n804: \n805: echo \"Running security vulnerability scans...\"\n806: \n807: # Test 1: Trivy scan\n808: echo \"Test 1: Trivy scan\"\n809: docker run --rm -v /var/run/docker.sock:/var/run/docker.sock \\\n810:   aquasec/trivy image \\\n811:   --severity HIGH,CRITICAL \\\n812:   --exit-code 1 \\\n813:   agentcube:latest\n814: \n815: # Test 2: Docker Scout scan\n816: echo \"Test 2: Docker Scout scan\"\n817: docker scout cves agentcube:latest\n818: \n819: # Test 3: Non-root user verification\n820: echo \"Test 3: Non-root user verification\"\n821: USER=$(docker run --rm agentcube:latest whoami)\n822: [ \"$USER\" != \"root\" ] || { echo \"ERROR: Container running as root\"; exit 1; }\n823: \n824: # Test 4: Sensitive data check\n825: echo \"Test 4: Sensitive data check\"\n826: docker history agentcube:latest | grep -i \"password\\|secret\\|key\" && \\\n827:   { echo \"ERROR: Potential sensitive data found\"; exit 1; }\n828: \n829: echo \"Security tests passed!\"\n830: ```\n831: \n832: ## Security Considerations\n833: \n834: ### Image Security\n835: \n836: 1. **Base Image Selection**\n837:    - Use official images from Docker Hub\n838:    - Pin specific versions (e.g., `alpine:3.19` not `alpine:latest`)\n839:    - Regularly update base images\n840:    - Monitor security advisories\n841: \n842: 2. **Minimal Attack Surface**\n843:    - Remove build tools and compilers from runtime image\n844:    - Use minimal base image (Alpine)\n845:    - Include only necessary runtime dependencies\n846:    - Avoid unnecessary packages\n847: \n848: 3. **Non-Privileged Execution**\n849:    - Run as non-root user (UID 1000)\n850:    - Use minimal capabilities\n851:    - Implement read-only root filesystem (optional)\n852:    - Drop all Linux capabilities\n853: \n854: ### Build Security\n855: \n856: 1. **Secrets Management**\n857:    - Never embed secrets in Dockerfile\n858:    - Use `.dockerignore` to exclude sensitive files\n859:    - Pass secrets at runtime via environment variables or secrets management\n860:    - Use multi-stage builds to exclude build-time secrets\n861: \n862: 2. **Dependency Security**\n863:    - Pin specific dependency versions\n864:    - Regularly update dependencies\n865:    - Scan dependencies for vulnerabilities\n866:    - Use signed packages when available\n867: \n868: 3. **Build Context**\n869:    - Minimize build context with `.dockerignore`\n870:    - Exclude unnecessary files and directories\n871:    - Separate source from build artifacts\n872:    - Use build arguments for configuration\n873: \n874: ### Runtime Security\n875: \n876: 1. **Container Security Context**\n877:    ```dockerfile\n878:    USER agentcube\n879:    ```\n880:    - Run as non-privileged user\n881:    - Use read-only root filesystem (optional)\n882:    - Drop Linux capabilities\n883:    - Configure seccomp profiles\n884: \n885: 2. **Network Security**\n886:    - Expose only necessary ports\n887:    - Use network policies\n888:    - Implement TLS for external communication\n889:    - Limit container network access\n890: \n891: 3. **Resource Limits**\n892:    - Set CPU and memory limits\n893:    - Implement resource quotas\n894:    - Monitor resource usage\n895:    - Prevent resource exhaustion\n896: \n897: ### Security Scanning\n898: \n899: ```bash\n900: # Trivy vulnerability scan\n901: docker run --rm -v /var/run/docker.sock:/var/run/docker.sock \\\n902:   aquasec/trivy image \\\n903:   --severity HIGH,CRITICAL \\\n904:   agentcube:latest\n905: \n906: # Docker Scout CVEs\n907: docker scout cves agentcube:latest\n908: \n909: # Hadolint best practices\n910: docker run --rm -i hadolint/hadolint hadolint < Dockerfile\n911: ```\n912: \n913: ## Performance Optimization\n914: \n915: ### Build Optimization\n916: \n917: 1. **Layer Caching Strategy**\n918:    - Order instructions from least to most frequently changing\n919:    - Copy dependency files before source code\n920:    - Use build arguments for version control\n921:    - Separate dependency installation from application copy\n922: \n923: 2. **Multi-Stage Optimization**\n924:    - Minimize artifact transfer between stages\n925:    - Use `.dockerignore` to reduce build context\n926:    - Combine related commands in single RUN instruction\n927:    - Clean up temporary files in each stage\n928: \n929: 3. **Build Parallelization**\n930:    ```bash\n931:    # Use BuildKit for parallel builds\n932:    DOCKER_BUILDKIT=1 docker build -t agentcube:latest .\n933:    ```\n934: \n935: ### Runtime Optimization\n936: \n937: 1. **Image Size Reduction**\n938:    - Use Alpine base image (~5MB)\n939:    - Remove package manager caches\n940:    - Use `--no-cache-dir` for pip\n941:    - Strip debug symbols from binaries\n942:    - Compress assets\n943: \n944: 2. **Startup Time Optimization**\n945:    - Minimize entrypoint script complexity\n946:    - Use compiled binaries instead of interpreters\n947:    - Pre-initialize common resources\n948:    - Implement lazy loading\n949: \n950: 3. **Memory Optimization**\n951:    - Use minimal runtime dependencies\n952:    - Implement connection pooling\n953:    - Optimize garbage collection settings\n954:    - Monitor memory usage patterns\n955: \n956: ## Monitoring and Metrics\n957: \n958: ### Build Metrics\n959: \n960: | Metric | Description | Target |\n961: |--------|-------------|--------|\n962: | Build Time | Time to complete build | < 5 minutes (cached) |\n963: | Image Size | Final image size | < 250 MB |\n964: | Layer Count | Number of layers | < 15 |\n965: | Cache Hit Rate | Percentage of cached layers | > 70% |\n966: \n967: ### Runtime Metrics\n968: \n969: | Metric | Description | Target |\n970: |--------|-------------|--------|\n971: | Startup Time | Time to become healthy | < 10 seconds |\n972: | Memory Usage | steady-state memory | < 200 MB |\n973: | CPU Usage | steady-state CPU | < 10% |\n974: | Health Check Response | Health endpoint latency | < 100ms |\n975: \n976: ### Metrics Collection\n977: \n978: ```dockerfile\n979: # Expose metrics endpoint\n980: EXPOSE 9090\n981: \n982: # Metrics configuration\n983: ENV AGENTCUBE_METRICS_ENABLED=true\n984: ENV AGENTCUBE_METRICS_PORT=9090\n985: ```\n986: \n987: Access metrics:\n988: ```\n989: curl http://localhost:9090/metrics\n990: ```\n991: \n992: ## Implementation Checklist\n993: \n994: ### Phase 1: Foundation\n995: - [ ] Create Dockerfile structure\n996: - [ ] Define build arguments\n997: - [ ] Configure .dockerignore\n998: - [ ] Set up base images\n999: \n1000: ### Phase 2: Builder Stage\n1001: - [ ] Install build tools\n1002: - [ ] Configure Go environment\n1003: - [ ] Implement Go dependency caching\n1004: - [ ] Compile agentd binary\n1005: - [ ] Configure Python environment\n1006: - [ ] Install Python dependencies\n1007: \n1008: ### Phase 3: Verifier Stage\n1009: - [ ] Implement test execution\n1010: - [ ] Configure code quality checks\n1011: - [ ] Set up test reporting\n1012: - [ ] Validate build artifacts\n1013: \n1014: ### Phase 4: Runtime Stage\n1015: - [ ] Configure Alpine base\n1016: - [ ] Install runtime dependencies\n1017: - [ ] Create non-privileged user\n1018: - [ ] Copy build artifacts\n1019: - [ ] Set up health checks\n1020: - [ ] Configure security context\n1021: \n1022: ### Phase 5: Build Scripts\n1023: - [ ] Create build script\n1024: - [ ] Create multi-architecture build script\n1025: - [ ] Create validation scripts\n1026: - [ ] Create test scripts\n1027: \n1028: ### Phase 6: Documentation\n1029: - [ ] Write Dockerfile comments\n1030: - [ ] Create build guide\n1031: - [ ] Create usage guide\n1032: - [ ] Document troubleshooting steps\n1033: \n1034: ### Phase 7: Testing\n1035: - [ ] Implement unit tests\n1036: - [ ] Implement integration tests\n1037: - [ ] Implement performance tests\n1038: - [ ] Implement security tests\n1039: \n1040: ## References\n1041: \n1042: - [Docker Multi-stage Builds](https://docs.docker.com/build/building/multi-stage/)\n1043: - [Docker Best Practices](https://docs.docker.com/develop/dev-best-practices/)\n1044: - [Alpine Linux](https://alpinelinux.org/)\n1045: - [Docker Buildx](https://docs.docker.com/buildx/working-with-buildx/)\n1046: - [Hadolint](https://github.com/hadolint/hadolint)\n1047: - [Trivy](https://github.com/aquasecurity/trivy)\n1048: - [Docker Scout](https://docs.docker.com/scout/)\n1049: - [AgentCube Project](../README.md)\n\n(End of file - total 1049 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-032: Dockerfile 多阶段构建 — Design Document\n\n## Overview\n\nThis design document outlines the technical implementation of a multi-stage Dockerfile build strategy for the AgentCube project. The implementation uses three independent build stages to create optimized production images, significantly reducing image size, improving build efficiency, enhancing security, and providing flexible image variants for different use cases.\n\n**Module:** `docker`  \n**Language:** Dockerfile  \n**Source Root:** `/changes/AR-032/`  \n**Size:** S\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Multi-Stage Build Architecture\n\nThe implementation follows a three-stage build architecture:\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                     Build Pipeline                          │","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-032/design.md","time":{"start":1775883129908,"end":1775883129927}}}}
