{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775883261631,"sessionID":"ses_2851e3b7cffetDjglBtQhaUd1M","part":{"id":"prt_d7ae4164c001r9guTggPsRGjtm","messageID":"msg_d7ae25597001plKz50AHaIE9fW","sessionID":"ses_2851e3b7cffetDjglBtQhaUd1M","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-6c81da7deee141d4af90958fc4472b43","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-032 — Dockerfile 多阶段构建 (3 images) Tasks\n\n**Module**: `docker`\n**Language**: Dockerfile\n**Size**: S\n**Design Stage**: ST-3 Completed\n\n## Task Breakdown\n\n### Task 1: Create .dockerignore file\n- [ ] Create .dockerignore file in project root\n- [ ] Add .git directory to exclude\n- [ ] Add *.md files to exclude (README.md, docs/)\n- [ ] Add test files (*_test.go, pytest.ini, .coverage)\n- [ ] Add development files (.vscode/, .idea/, *.swp)\n- [ ] Add build artifacts (dist/, build/, *.exe)\n- [ ] Add CI/CD files (.github/, .gitlab-ci.yml)\n- [ ] Add OS files (.DS_Store, Thumbs.db)\n- [ ] Add temporary files (tmp/, temp/, *.tmp)\n- [ ] Add .dockerignore itself to exclude\n\n**Verification**:\n```bash\ntest -f .dockerignore && echo \".dockerignore exists\" || echo \"Missing\"\ngrep -q \"\\.git\" .dockerignore && echo \"Git excluded\" || echo \"Git not excluded\"\ngrep -q \"*_test\\.go\" .dockerignore && echo \"Test files excluded\" || echo \"Test files not excluded\"\n```\n\n**Acceptance Criteria**:\n- .dockerignore file exists in project root\n- Contains all required exclusion patterns\n- Build context is minimized (verify with docker build context size)\n\n---\n\n### Task 2: Create Dockerfile build arguments section\n- [ ] Create Dockerfile in project root\n- [ ] Add ARG GO_VERSION with default value 1.21\n- [ ] Add ARG ALPINE_VERSION with default value 3.19\n- [ ] Add ARG BUILD_VERSION with default value dev\n- [ ] Add ARG BUILD_TIME for build timestamp\n- [ ] Add ARG GIT_COMMIT for git commit hash\n- [ ] Add comment block explaining build arguments\n- [ ] Document build argument usage\n\n**Verification**:\n```bash\ngrep -q \"ARG GO_VERSION=1.21\" Dockerfile && echo \"GO_VERSION defined\" || echo \"Missing\"\ngrep -q \"ARG BUILD_VERSION=dev\" Dockerfile && echo \"BUILD_VERSION defined\" || echo \"Missing\"\ngrep -q \"ARG BUILD_TIME\" Dockerfile && echo \"BUILD_TIME defined\" || echo \"Missing\"\ngrep -q \"ARG GIT_COMMIT\" Dockerfile && echo \"GIT_COMMIT defined\" || echo \"Missing\"\n```\n\n**Acceptance Criteria**:\n- All 5 build arguments are defined\n- Default values are set for GO_VERSION, ALPINE_VERSION, BUILD_VERSION\n- Comments explain each build argument's purpose\n\n---\n\n### Task 3: Create builder stage FROM statement\n- [ ] Add builder stage FROM statement using golang:${GO_VERSION}-alpine\n- [ ] Name the stage AS builder\n- [ ] Add comment describing builder stage purpose\n- [ ] Copy build arguments into builder stage (BUILD_VERSION, BUILD_TIME, GIT_COMMIT)\n\n**Verification**:\n```bash\ngrep -q \"FROM golang:\\${GO_VERSION}-alpine AS builder\" Dockerfile && echo \"Builder FROM correct\" || echo \"Builder FROM incorrect\"\n```\n\n**Acceptance Criteria**:\n- Builder stage uses golang:1.21-alpine base image\n- Stage is named \"builder\"\n- Comment describes stage purpose\n- Build arguments are available in builder stage\n\n---\n\n### Task 4: Install build tools in builder stage\n- [ ] Add RUN apk add --no-cache command\n- [ ] Install python3 package\n- [ ] Install py3-pip package\n- [ ] Install gcc package\n- [ ] Install musl-dev package\n- [ ] Install git package\n- [ ] Combine all packages in single RUN instruction for layer optimization\n- [ ] Clean up package cache in same RUN instruction\n\n**Verification**:\n```bash\ngrep -A 3 \"RUN apk add --no-cache\" Dockerfile | grep -q \"python3\" && echo \"Python installed\" || echo \"Python missing\"\ngrep -A 3 \"RUN apk add --no-cache\" Dockerfile | grep -q \"gcc\" && echo \"GCC installed\" || echo \"GCC missing\"\n```\n\n**Acceptance Criteria**:\n- All required build tools are installed\n- Single RUN instruction with --no-cache flag\n- Package cache is cleaned up\n\n---\n\n### Task 5: Set working directory in builder stage\n- [ ] Add WORKDIR /build instruction\n- [ ] Add comment explaining working directory choice\n\n**Verification**:\n```bash\ngrep -q \"WORKDIR /build\" Dockerfile && echo \"Working directory set\" || echo \"Working directory missing\"\n```\n\n**Acceptance Criteria**:\n- Working directory is set to /build\n- Comment explains the choice\n\n---\n\n### Task 6: Copy Go dependencies for caching optimization\n- [ ] Add COPY go.mod go.sum ./ instruction\n- [ ] Add comment explaining caching optimization\n- [ ] Add RUN go mod download instruction\n- [ ] Verify dependency manifests are copied before source code\n\n**Verification**:\n```bash\ngrep -q \"COPY go.mod go.sum \\./\" Dockerfile && echo \"Go deps copied first\" || echo \"Go deps not first\"\ngrep -q \"RUN go mod download\" Dockerfile && echo \"Go mod download present\" || echo \"Go mod download missing\"\n```\n\n**Acceptance Criteria**:\n- go.mod and go.sum are copied before source code\n- go mod download is run immediately after copying manifests\n- Comment explains caching optimization\n\n---\n\n### Task 7: Copy Go source code\n- [ ] Add COPY ./pkg ./pkg instruction\n- [ ] Add COPY ./cmd ./cmd instruction\n- [ ] Add comment explaining source code structure\n- [ ] Ensure source code is copied after dependencies are installed\n\n**Verification**:\n```bash\ngrep -q \"COPY \\./pkg \\./pkg\" Dockerfile && echo \"pkg copied\" || echo \"pkg not copied\"\ngrep -q \"COPY \\./cmd \\./cmd\" Dockerfile && echo \"cmd copied\" || echo \"cmd not copied\"\n```\n\n**Acceptance Criteria**:\n- pkg directory is copied\n- cmd directory is copied\n- Source code is copied after dependency installation\n\n---\n\n### Task 8: Build agentd binary with version info\n- [ ] Add RUN go build instruction\n- [ ] Set CGO_ENABLED=0 environment variable\n- [ ] Set GOOS=linux environment variable\n- [ ] Add -ldflags=\"-s -w\" for binary size optimization\n- [ ] Add -X main.Version=${BUILD_VERSION} to embed version\n- [ ] Add -X main.BuildTime=${BUILD_TIME} to embed build time\n- [ ] Add -X main.GitCommit=${GIT_COMMIT} to embed commit hash\n- [ ] Set output path as -o agentd\n- [ ] Set build path as ./cmd/agentd\n- [ ] Add comment explaining build flags and version embedding\n\n**Verification**:\n```bash\ngrep -q \"CGO_ENABLED=0 GOOS=linux go build\" Dockerfile && echo \"Go build correct\" || echo \"Go build incorrect\"\ngrep -q \"main.Version=\\${BUILD_VERSION}\" Dockerfile && echo \"Version embedding\" || echo \"Version not embedded\"\ngrep -q \"-ldflags=\\\"-s -w\\\"\" Dockerfile && echo \"Size optimization\" || echo \"Size optimization missing\"\n```\n\n**Acceptance Criteria**:\n- Binary is built with CGO_ENABLED=0 and GOOS=linux\n- -s -w flags are used for size optimization\n- Version, build time, and commit are embedded\n- Output binary is named agentd\n\n---\n\n### Task 9: Copy Python source and requirements\n- [ ] Add COPY ./cmd/picod /build/picod instruction\n- [ ] Add COPY requirements.txt ./ instruction\n- [ ] Add comment explaining Python component structure\n- [ ] Ensure Python dependencies are copied after Go source code\n\n**Verification**:\n```bash\ngrep -q \"COPY \\./cmd/picod /build/picod\" Dockerfile && echo \"Python source copied\" || echo \"Python source missing\"\ngrep -q \"COPY requirements\\.txt \\./\" Dockerfile && echo \"Requirements copied\" || echo \"Requirements missing\"\n```\n\n**Acceptance Criteria**:\n- picod source directory is copied\n- requirements.txt is copied\n- Comment explains Python component structure\n\n---\n\n### Task 10: Install Python dependencies\n- [ ] Add RUN pip install instruction\n- [ ] Use --no-cache-dir flag to reduce image size\n- [ ] Install from requirements.txt with -r requirements.txt\n- [ ] Add comment explaining --no-cache-dir optimization\n\n**Verification**:\n```bash\ngrep -q \"RUN pip install --no-cache-dir -r requirements\\.txt\" Dockerfile && echo \"Python deps installed\" || echo \"Python deps missing\"\n```\n\n**Acceptance Criteria**:\n- Python dependencies are installed from requirements.txt\n- --no-cache-dir flag is used\n- Comment explains optimization\n\n---\n\n### Task 11: Create verifier stage (optional)\n- [ ] Add verifier stage FROM builder AS verifier\n- [ ] Add comment describing verifier stage purpose\n- [ ] Add RUN go test ./... -v -coverprofile=coverage.out instruction\n- [ ] Add RUN pytest /build/picod/tests -v instruction\n- [ ] Add RUN go tool cover -html=coverage.out -o coverage.html instruction\n- [ ] Add comments explaining each test execution\n\n**Verification**:\n```bash\ngrep -q \"FROM builder AS verifier\" Dockerfile && echo \"Verifier stage created\" || echo \"Verifier stage missing\"\ngrep -q \"RUN go test \\./\\.\\.\\. -v -coverprofile=coverage\\.out\" Dockerfile && echo \"Go tests configured\" || echo \"Go tests missing\"\ngrep -q \"RUN pytest /build/picod/tests -v\" Dockerfile && echo \"Python tests configured\" || echo \"Python tests missing\"\n```\n\n**Acceptance Criteria**:\n- Verifier stage inherits from builder\n- Go tests are configured\n- Python tests are configured\n- Coverage reports are generated\n\n---\n\n### Task 12: Create runtime stage FROM statement\n- [ ] Add runtime stage FROM alpine:${ALPINE_VERSION} AS runtime\n- [ ] Copy build arguments into runtime stage (BUILD_VERSION, GIT_COMMIT)\n- [ ] Add comment describing runtime stage purpose\n\n**Verification**:\n```bash\ngrep -q \"FROM alpine:\\${ALPINE_VERSION} AS runtime\" Dockerfile && echo \"Runtime FROM correct\" || echo \"Runtime FROM incorrect\"\n```\n\n**Acceptance Criteria**:\n- Runtime stage uses alpine:3.19 base image\n- Stage is named \"runtime\"\n- Build arguments are available for labeling\n\n---\n\n### Task 13: Add image metadata labels\n- [ ] Add LABEL maintainer=\"agentcube@volcano.sh\"\n- [ ] Add LABEL version=\"${BUILD_VERSION}\"\n- [ ] Add LABEL git.commit=\"${GIT_COMMIT}\"\n- [ ] Add LABEL description=\"AgentCube Runtime Image\"\n- [ ] Add comment explaining label purpose\n\n**Verification**:\n```bash\ngrep -q \"LABEL maintainer=\" Dockerfile && echo \"Maintainer label\" || echo \"Maintainer missing\"\ngrep -q \"LABEL version=\" Dockerfile && echo \"Version label\" || echo \"Version missing\"\ngrep -q \"LABEL git.commit=\" Dockerfile && echo \"Git commit label\" || echo \"Git commit missing\"\n```\n\n**Acceptance Criteria**:\n- All 4 labels are defined\n- Labels use build arguments for versioning\n- Comment explains label purpose\n\n---\n\n### Task 14: Install runtime dependencies in runtime stage\n- [ ] Add RUN apk add --no-cache instruction\n- [ ] Install ca-certificates package\n- [ ] Install python3 package\n- [ ] Install py3-pip package\n- [ ] Install tzdata package\n- [ ] Add RUN update-ca-certificates instruction\n- [ ] Combine all in single RUN instruction\n- [ ] Clean up package cache in same RUN instruction\n\n**Verification**:\n```bash\ngrep -A 5 \"RUN apk add --no-cache\" Dockerfile | grep -q \"ca-certificates\" && echo \"ca-certificates installed\" || echo \"ca-certificates missing\"\ngrep -A 5 \"RUN apk add --no-cache\" Dockerfile | grep -q \"tzdata\" && echo \"tzdata installed\" || echo \"tzdata missing\"\n```\n\n**Acceptance Criteria**:\n- Runtime dependencies are installed (ca-certificates, python3, py3-pip, tzdata)\n- CA certificates are updated\n- Single RUN instruction with cleanup\n\n---\n\n### Task 15: Create non-privileged user in runtime stage\n- [ ] Add RUN addgroup -g 1000 agentcube instruction\n- [ ] Add RUN adduser -D -u 1000 -G agentcube agentcube instruction\n- [ ] Combine both commands in single RUN instruction\n- [ ] Add comment explaining non-root user configuration\n\n**Verification**:\n```bash\ngrep -q \"addgroup -g 1000 agentcube\" Dockerfile && echo \"Group created\" || echo \"Group missing\"\ngrep -q \"adduser -D -u 1000 -G agentcube agentcube\" Dockerfile && echo \"User created\" || echo \"User missing\"\n```\n\n**Acceptance Criteria**:\n- agentcube group is created with GID 1000\n- agentcube user is created with UID 1000\n- User is added to agentcube group\n- Comment explains security benefit\n\n---\n\n### Task 16: Set working directory in runtime stage\n- [ ] Add WORKDIR /app instruction\n- [ ] Add comment explaining working directory choice\n\n**Verification**:\n```bash\ngrep -q \"WORKDIR /app\" Dockerfile && echo \"App working directory set\" || echo \"Working directory missing\"\n```\n\n**Acceptance Criteria**:\n- Working directory is set to /app\n- Comment explains the choice\n\n---\n\n### Task 17: Copy compiled binary from builder stage\n- [ ] Add COPY --from=builder /build/agentd /app/agentd instruction\n- [ ] Add comment explaining artifact transfer from builder stage\n\n**Verification**:\n```bash\ngrep -q \"COPY --from=builder /build/agentd /app/agentd\" Dockerfile && echo \"Binary copied\" || echo \"Binary not copied\"\n```\n\n**Acceptance Criteria**:\n- agentd binary is copied from builder stage\n- Binary is placed in /app directory\n- Comment explains multi-stage artifact transfer\n\n---\n\n### Task 18: Copy Python environment from builder stage\n- [ ] Add COPY --from=builder /usr/local/lib/python3.11/site-packages /usr/local/lib/python3.11/site-packages instruction\n- [ ] Add COPY --from=builder /build/picod /app/picod instruction\n- [ ] Add comment explaining Python environment transfer\n\n**Verification**:\n```bash\ngrep -q \"COPY --from=builder /usr/local/lib/python3.11/site-packages\" Dockerfile && echo \"Python site-packages copied\" || echo \"Python site-packages missing\"\ngrep -q \"COPY --from=builder /build/picod /app/picod\" Dockerfile && echo \"picod copied\" || echo \"picod missing\"\n```\n\n**Acceptance Criteria**:\n- Python site-packages are copied from builder stage\n- picod source directory is copied from builder stage\n- Comment explains multi-stage transfer\n\n---\n\n### Task 19: Set file ownership for non-privileged user\n- [ ] Add RUN chown -R agentcube:agentcube /app instruction\n- [ ] Add comment explaining security context\n\n**Verification**:\n```bash\ngrep -q \"chown -R agentcube:agentcube /app\" Dockerfile && echo \"Ownership set\" || echo \"Ownership not set\"\n```\n\n**Acceptance Criteria**:\n- All files in /app are owned by agentcube:agentcube\n- Comment explains security benefit\n\n---\n\n### Task 20: Switch to non-privileged user in runtime stage\n- [ ] Add USER agentcube instruction\n- [ ] Add comment explaining non-root execution\n\n**Verification**:\n```bash\ngrep -q \"USER agentcube\" Dockerfile && echo \"Non-root user set\" || echo \"Non-root user missing\"\n```\n\n**Acceptance Criteria**:\n- Container runs as agentcube user\n- Comment explains security benefit\n\n---\n\n### Task 21: Expose ports in runtime stage\n- [ ] Add EXPOSE 8080 instruction\n- [ ] Add EXPOSE 9090 instruction\n- [ ] Add comment explaining port usage (8080 for API, 9090 for metrics)\n\n**Verification**:\n```bash\ngrep -q \"EXPOSE 8080\" Dockerfile && echo \"Port 8080 exposed\" || echo \"Port 8080 missing\"\ngrep -q \"EXPOSE 9090\" Dockerfile && echo \"Port 9090 exposed\" || echo \"Port 9090 missing\"\n```\n\n**Acceptance Criteria**:\n- Port 8080 is exposed\n- Port 9090 is exposed\n- Comment explains each port's purpose\n\n---\n\n### Task 22: Configure health check in runtime stage\n- [ ] Add HEALTHCHECK instruction\n- [ ] Set --interval=30s parameter\n- [ ] Set --timeout=10s parameter\n- [ ] Set --start-period=5s parameter\n- [ ] Set --retries=3 parameter\n- [ ] Add CMD agentd health || exit 1\n- [ ] Add comment explaining health check configuration\n\n**Verification**:\n```bash\ngrep -q \"HEALTHCHECK\" Dockerfile && echo \"Healthcheck configured\" || echo \"Healthcheck missing\"\ngrep -q \"agentd health\" Dockerfile && echo \"Health check command\" || echo \"Health check command missing\"\n```\n\n**Acceptance Criteria**:\n- HEALTHCHECK is configured with all parameters\n- Check command runs agentd health\n- Comment explains configuration\n\n---\n\n### Task 23: Set entry point in runtime stage\n- [ ] Add ENTRYPOINT [\"/app/agentd\"] instruction\n- [ ] Add comment explaining entry point choice\n\n**Verification**:\n```bash\ngrep -q \"ENTRYPOINT \\[\\\"/app/agentd\\\"\\]\" Dockerfile && echo \"Entrypoint set\" || echo \"Entrypoint missing\"\n```\n\n**Acceptance Criteria**:\n- Entry point points to /app/agentd binary\n- Array format is used for proper signal handling\n- Comment explains entry point choice\n\n---\n\n### Task 24: Test production image build\n- [ ] Run docker build command without --target flag\n- [ ] Set BUILD_VERSION argument to test value\n- [ ] Set BUILD_TIME argument to current timestamp\n- [ ] Set GIT_COMMIT argument to test commit\n- [ ] Tag image as agentcube:latest\n- [ ] Verify build completes successfully\n- [ ] Verify image is created\n\n**Verification**:\n```bash\ndocker build \\\n  --build-arg BUILD_VERSION=1.0.0 \\\n  --build-arg BUILD_TIME=$(date -u +%Y-%m-%dT%H:%M:%SZ) \\\n  --build-arg GIT_COMMIT=abc123 \\\n  -t agentcube:latest \\\n  .\ndocker images | grep agentcube:latest\n```\n\n**Acceptance Criteria**:\n- Production image builds successfully\n- Image is tagged as agentcube:latest\n- Build arguments are applied correctly\n\n---\n\n### Task 25: Test builder image build\n- [ ] Run docker build command with --target builder flag\n- [ ] Tag image as agentcube:dev\n- [ ] Verify build completes successfully\n- [ ] Verify image is created\n- [ ] Verify image contains build tools (gcc, go, python)\n\n**Verification**:\n```bash\ndocker build --target builder -t agentcube:dev .\ndocker run --rm agentcube:dev which go\ndocker run --rm agentcube:dev which gcc\ndocker run --rm agentcube:dev which python3\n```\n\n**Acceptance Criteria**:\n- Builder image builds successfully\n- Image is tagged as agentcube:dev\n- Build tools are present in image\n\n---\n\n### Task 26: Test verifier image build\n- [ ] Run docker build command with --target verifier flag\n- [ ] Tag image as agentcube:test\n- [ ] Verify build completes successfully\n- [ ] Verify image is created\n- [ ] Verify tests are executed during build\n\n**Verification**:\n```bash\ndocker build --target verifier -t agentcube:test .\ndocker images | grep agentcube:test\n```\n\n**Acceptance Criteria**:\n- Verifier image builds successfully\n- Image is tagged as agentcube:test\n- Tests are executed in verifier stage\n\n---\n\n### Task 27: Verify production image size\n- [ ] Measure production image size\n- [ ] Verify size is under 250 MB\n- [ ] Compare with builder image size\n- [ ] Verify size reduction is significant (>50%)\n- [ ] Document image sizes\n\n**Verification**:\n```bash\ndocker images agentcube:latest --format \"{{.Size}}\"\ndocker images agentcube:dev --format \"{{.Size}}\"\n```\n\n**Acceptance Criteria**:\n- Production image size < 250 MB\n- Production image is at least 50% smaller than builder image\n- Sizes are documented\n\n---\n\n### Task 28: Verify non-root user in production image\n- [ ] Run container from production image\n- [ ] Execute whoami command\n- [ ] Verify user is agentcube (not root)\n- [ ] Verify user ID is 1000\n- [ ] Verify group ID is 1000\n\n**Verification**:\n```bash\ndocker run --rm agentcube:latest whoami\ndocker run --rm agentcube:latest id\n```\n\n**Acceptance Criteria**:\n- Container runs as agentcube user\n- User ID is 1000\n- Group ID is 1000\n- Not running as root\n\n---\n\n### Task 29: Verify build tools are not in production image\n- [ ] Run container from production image\n- [ ] Check for go binary\n- [ ] Check for gcc binary\n- [ ] Check for python-dev packages\n- [ ] Verify build tools are absent\n\n**Verification**:\n```bash\ndocker run --rm agentcube:latest which go || echo \"Go not found (expected)\"\ndocker run --rm agentcube:latest which gcc || echo \"GCC not found (expected)\"\n```\n\n**Acceptance Criteria**:\n- go binary is not present\n- gcc binary is not present\n- Development packages are not present\n- Only runtime dependencies are present\n\n---\n\n### Task 30: Verify version information in binary\n- [ ] Run container from production image\n- [ ] Execute agentd version command\n- [ ] Verify version matches BUILD_VERSION argument\n- [ ] Verify build time is embedded\n- [ ] Verify git commit is embedded\n\n**Verification**:\n```bash\ndocker run --rm agentcube:latest /app/agentd version\n```\n\n**Acceptance Criteria**:\n- Version information is displayed\n- Version matches BUILD_VERSION argument\n- Build time is embedded\n- Git commit is embedded\n\n---\n\n### Task 31: Test container startup\n- [ ] Run container in background with docker run -d\n- [ ] Wait for container to start\n- [ ] Check container status\n- [ ] Verify container is running\n- [ ] Check container logs\n\n**Verification**:\n```bash\nCONTAINER_ID=$(docker run -d agentcube:latest)\nsleep 10\ndocker inspect --format='{{.State.Status}}' $CONTAINER_ID\ndocker logs $CONTAINER_ID\ndocker stop $CONTAINER_ID\n```\n\n**Acceptance Criteria**:\n- Container starts successfully\n- Container status is \"running\"\n- No errors in container logs\n- Application is initialized\n\n---\n\n### Task 32: Test health check\n- [ ] Run container in background\n- [ ] Wait for health check to run\n- [ ] Check container health status\n- [ ] Verify health status is \"healthy\"\n- [ ] Verify health check is working\n\n**Verification**:\n```bash\nCONTAINER_ID=$(docker run -d agentcube:latest)\nsleep 30\ndocker inspect --format='{{.State.Health.Status}}' $CONTAINER_ID\ndocker stop $CONTAINER_ID\n```\n\n**Acceptance Criteria**:\n- Health check runs\n- Health status is \"healthy\"\n- Health check interval is 30s\n- Health check timeout is 10s\n\n---\n\n### Task 33: Test port exposure\n- [ ] Run container with published ports\n- [ ] Publish port 8080\n- [ ] Publish port 9090\n- [ ] Test connectivity to port 8080\n- [ ] Test connectivity to port 9090\n- [ ] Verify health endpoint is accessible\n\n**Verification**:\n```bash\nCONTAINER_ID=$(docker run -d -p 8080:8080 -p 9090:9090 agentcube:latest)\nsleep 10\ncurl -f http://localhost:8080/healthz || echo \"Port 8080 accessible\"\ncurl -f http://localhost:9090/metrics || echo \"Port 9090 accessible\"\ndocker stop $CONTAINER_ID\n```\n\n**Acceptance Criteria**:\n- Port 8080 is accessible\n- Port 9090 is accessible\n- Health endpoint responds\n- Metrics endpoint responds\n\n---\n\n### Task 34: Verify Dockerfile syntax with linter\n- [ ] Install hadolint\n- [ ] Run hadolint on Dockerfile\n- [ ] Fix any linting errors\n- [ ] Fix any linting warnings\n- [ ] Verify no critical issues remain\n\n**Verification**:\n```bash\ndocker run --rm -i hadolint/hadolint hadolint < Dockerfile\n```\n\n**Acceptance Criteria**:\n- Hadolint passes without errors\n- No critical warnings remain\n- Dockerfile follows best practices\n\n---\n\n### Task 35: Verify Dockerfile layer optimization\n- [ ] Inspect Dockerfile layer order\n- [ ] Verify stable instructions appear first\n- [ ] Verify frequently changing instructions appear last\n- [ ] Verify dependency installation is before source code copy\n- [ ] Verify commands are combined where possible\n\n**Verification**:\n```bash\ndocker history agentcube:latest\n```\n\n**Acceptance Criteria**:\n- Stable base image layers are first\n- Dependency layers come before source code\n- Related commands are combined\n- Layer count is minimized (< 15 layers)\n\n---\n\n### Task 36: Test build caching\n- [ ] Perform initial build and measure time\n- [ ] Perform second build without changes\n- [ ] Measure cache hit rate\n- [ ] Verify second build is faster\n- [ ] Verify layers are cached correctly\n\n**Verification**:\n```bash\ntime docker build -t agentcube:cache1 . 2>&1 | tee build1.log\ntime docker build -t agentcube:cache2 . 2>&1 | tee build2.log\ngrep -i \"cache\" build2.log\n```\n\n**Acceptance Criteria**:\n- Second build is significantly faster\n- Cache hit rate > 70%\n- Layers are reused where possible\n\n---\n\n### Task 37: Create build script\n- [ ] Create scripts/build.sh\n- [ ] Add build arguments handling\n- [ ] Add image tagging logic\n- [ ] Add version argument\n- [ ] Add dry-run option\n- [ ] Add multi-architecture build support\n- [ ] Make script executable\n\n**Verification**:\n```bash\ntest -f scripts/build.sh && echo \"Build script exists\" || echo \"Build script missing\"\ntest -x scripts/build.sh && echo \"Script executable\" || echo \"Script not executable\"\n```\n\n**Acceptance Criteria**:\n- Build script exists in scripts/ directory\n- Script is executable\n- Script handles build arguments\n- Script supports multiple architectures\n\n---\n\n### Task 38: Test multi-architecture build\n- [ ] Create buildx builder\n- [ ] Build for linux/amd64 platform\n- [ ] Build for linux/arm64 platform\n- [ ] Verify both architectures build successfully\n- [ ] Test both images run correctly\n- [ ] Clean up buildx builder\n\n**Verification**:\n```bash\ndocker buildx create --name agentcube-builder --use\ndocker buildx build --platform linux/amd64 -t agentcube:amd64 --load .\ndocker buildx build --platform linux/arm64 -t agentcube:arm64 --load .\ndocker buildx rm agentcube-builder\n```\n\n**Acceptance Criteria**:\n- linux/amd64 image builds successfully\n- linux/arm64 image builds successfully\n- Both images run on respective platforms\n- Cross-compilation works correctly\n\n---\n\n### Task 39: Verify image security with vulnerability scan\n- [ ] Install trivy\n- [ ] Run trivy scan on production image\n- [ ] Check for HIGH severity vulnerabilities\n- [ ] Check for CRITICAL severity vulnerabilities\n- [ ] Document any vulnerabilities found\n- [ ] Address any security issues\n\n**Verification**:\n```bash\ndocker run --rm -v /var/run/docker.sock:/var/run/docker.sock \\\n  aquasec/trivy image --severity HIGH,CRITICAL agentcube:latest\n```\n\n**Acceptance Criteria**:\n- No CRITICAL vulnerabilities (or documented and accepted)\n- No HIGH vulnerabilities (or documented and accepted)\n- Vulnerability report is generated\n- Security posture is documented\n\n---\n\n### Task 40: Verify reproducible builds\n- [ ] Build image with specific versions\n- [ ] Record image digest\n- [ ] Build image again with same parameters\n- [ ] Compare image digests\n- [ ] Verify digests are identical\n\n**Verification**:\n```bash\nDIGEST1=$(docker build --quiet -t agentcube:repro1 .)\nDIGEST2=$(docker build --quiet -t agentcube:repro2 .)\necho \"Digest 1: $DIGEST1\"\necho \"Digest 2: $DIGEST2\"\n[ \"$DIGEST1\" = \"$DIGEST2\" ] && echo \"Builds are reproducible\" || echo \"Builds differ\"\n```\n\n**Acceptance Criteria**:\n- Both builds produce identical digests\n- Builds are deterministic\n- No random factors affect build output\n\n---\n\n### Task 41: Create documentation\n- [ ] Create docs/docker.md\n- [ ] Document build process\n- [ ] Document build arguments\n- [ ] Document image variants\n- [ ] Provide usage examples\n- [ ] Document health check endpoints\n- [ ] Document metrics endpoints\n\n**Verification**:\n```bash\ntest -f docs/docker.md && echo \"Documentation exists\" || echo \"Documentation missing\"\ngrep -q \"Build Process\" docs/docker.md && echo \"Build process documented\" || echo \"Build process not documented\"\n```\n\n**Acceptance Criteria**:\n- Documentation file exists\n- Build process is documented\n- Build arguments are documented\n- Usage examples are provided\n- API endpoints are documented\n\n---\n\n### Task 42: Update README.md\n- [ ] Update README.md with Docker build section\n- [ ] Add quick start instructions\n- [ ] Add build examples\n- [ ] Add run examples\n- [ ] Add multi-architecture build instructions\n- [ ] Add troubleshooting section\n\n**Verification**:\n```bash\ngrep -q \"Docker\" README.md && echo \"Docker section added\" || echo \"Docker section missing\"\ngrep -q \"docker build\" README.md && echo \"Build command documented\" || echo \"Build command not documented\"\n```\n\n**Acceptance Criteria**:\n- README.md has Docker build section\n- Quick start instructions are provided\n- Build examples are included\n- Troubleshooting section is added\n\n---\n\n### Task 43: Create .dockerfile documentation\n- [ ] Add comments to Dockerfile explaining each stage\n- [ ] Add comments explaining complex build steps\n- [ ] Add comments for non-obvious COPY commands\n- [ ] Add comments explaining optimization techniques\n- [ ] Ensure comments are clear and helpful\n\n**Verification**:\n```bash\ngrep -q \"# Stage 1: Builder\" Dockerfile && echo \"Builder stage commented\" || echo \"Builder stage not commented\"\ngrep -q \"# Multi-stage build\" Dockerfile && echo \"Multi-stage explained\" || echo \"Multi-stage not explained\"\n```\n\n**Acceptance Criteria**:\n- Each stage has a descriptive comment\n- Complex steps have explanatory comments\n- Optimization techniques are documented\n- Comments are clear and helpful\n\n---\n\n### Task 44: Verify build context size\n- [ ] Measure build context size\n- [ ] Verify .dockerignore is effective\n- [ ] Verify unnecessary files are excluded\n- [ ] Document build context size\n- [ ] Optimize if size is too large\n\n**Verification**:\n```bash\ndocker build --progress=plain -t agentcube:context . 2>&1 | grep -i \"context size\"\n```\n\n**Acceptance Criteria**:\n- Build context size is reasonable (< 100 MB)\n- Unnecessary files are excluded\n- .dockerignore is effective\n- Build context size is documented\n\n---\n\n### Task 45: Final integration test\n- [ ] Perform complete build pipeline\n- [ ] Build all three image variants\n- [ ] Run all three images\n- [ ] Verify all functionality works\n- [ ] Run all tests\n- [ ] Verify no errors\n- [ ] Document results\n\n**Verification**:\n```bash\ndocker build -t agentcube:latest .\ndocker build --target builder -t agentcube:dev .\ndocker build --target verifier -t agentcube:test .\ndocker images | grep agentcube\n```\n\n**Acceptance Criteria**:\n- All three variants build successfully\n- All images run correctly\n- All tests pass\n- No errors in build or runtime\n- Integration test results are documented\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\n**Total Tasks**: 45\n**Estimated Effort**: S (Small) - 8-12 hours\n\n### Key Deliverables\n1. **Multi-stage Dockerfile** with 3 stages (builder, verifier, runtime)\n2. **.dockerignore** file for build context optimization\n3. **Build scripts** for automated builds\n4. **Documentation** (docs/docker.md, README.md updates)\n5. **Testing validation** (unit, integration, security tests)\n\n### Success Criteria\n- All three Dockerfile stages are implemented correctly\n- Multi-stage build produces minimal runtime image (< 250 MB)\n- Production image size is at least 50% smaller than builder image\n- Non-root user is configured correctly\n- Build tools are excluded from production image\n- Health checks are configured and working\n- All tests pass\n- No critical security vulnerabilities\n- Multi-architecture builds work correctly\n- Documentation is complete\n\n### Dependencies\n- Docker 20.10+ (for multi-stage build support)\n- Go 1.21+ (for building AgentCube components)\n- Python 3.11+ (for picod component)\n- Base design document: `changes/AR-032/design.md`\n- Base specification document: `changes/AR-032/delta-spec.md`\n\n### Blocked By\n- None (design stage ST-3 completed)\n\n### Blocks\n- AR-033: Controller Manager Deployment (depends on Docker images)\n- AR-034: Workload Manager Deployment (depends on Docker images)\n- AR-035: Router Deployment (depends on Docker images)\n\n### Notes\n- Multi-stage builds are critical for security and image size optimization\n- Always use specific image versions, never `latest` tag\n- Follow Dockerfile best practices for layer optimization\n- Run security scans before deploying to production\n- Use buildx for multi-architecture builds\n- Document any exceptions to security best practices","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-032/tasks.md"},"output":"Wrote file success